            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"ph4\">1912<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"ph4\"><$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000022\">ACT 1</$link><br>\n<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000172\">ACT 2</$link><br>\n<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000510\">ACT 3</$link><br>\n<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000738\">ACT 4</$link><br>\n<$link class=\"pginternal\" to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000832\">ACT 5</$link><br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>PREFACE TO PYGMALION.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"ph4\">A Professor of Phonetics.</div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>As will be seen later on, Pygmalion needs, not a preface, but a sequel, which I have supplied in its due place. The English have no respect for their language, and will not teach their children to speak it. They spell it so abominably that no man can teach himself what it sounds like. It is impossible for an Englishman to open his mouth without making some other Englishman hate or despise him. German and Spanish are accessible to foreigners: English is not accessible even to Englishmen. The reformer England needs today is an energetic phonetic enthusiast: that is why I have made such a one the hero of a popular play. There have been heroes of that kind crying in the wilderness for many years past. When I became interested in the subject towards the end of the eighteen-seventies, Melville Bell was dead; but Alexander J. Ellis was still a living patriarch, with an impressive head always covered by a velvet skull cap, for which he would apologize to public meetings in a very courtly manner. He and Tito Pagliardini, another phonetic veteran, were men whom it was impossible to dislike. Henry Sweet, then a young man, lacked their sweetness of character: he was about as conciliatory to conventional mortals as Ibsen or Samuel Butler. His great ability as a phonetician (he was, I think, the best of them all at his job) would have entitled him to high official recognition, and perhaps enabled him to popularize his subject, but for his Satanic contempt for all academic dignitaries and persons in general who thought more of Greek than of phonetics. Once, in the days when the Imperial Institute rose in South Kensington, and Joseph Chamberlain was booming the Empire, I induced the editor of a leading monthly review to commission an article from Sweet on the imperial importance of his subject. When it arrived, it contained nothing but a savagely derisive attack on a professor of language and literature whose chair Sweet regarded as proper to a phonetic expert only. The article, being libelous, had to be returned as impossible; and I had to renounce my dream of dragging its author into the limelight. When I met him afterwards, for the first time for many years, I found to my astonishment that he, who had been a quite tolerably presentable young man, had actually managed by sheer scorn to alter his personal appearance until he had become a sort of walking repudiation of Oxford and all its traditions. It must have been largely in his own despite that he was squeezed into something called a Readership of phonetics there. The future of phonetics rests probably with his pupils, who all swore by him; but nothing could bring the man himself into any sort of compliance with the university, to which he nevertheless clung by divine right in an intensely Oxonian way. I daresay his papers, if he has left any, include some satires that may be published without too destructive results fifty years hence. He was, I believe, not in the least an ill-natured man: very much the opposite, I should say; but he would not suffer fools gladly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Those who knew him will recognize in my third act the allusion to the patent Shorthand in which he used to write postcards, and which may be acquired from a four and six-penny manual published by the Clarendon Press. The postcards which Mrs. Higgins describes are such as I have received from Sweet. I would decipher a sound which a cockney would represent by zerr, and a Frenchman by seu, and then write demanding with some heat what on earth it meant. Sweet, with boundless contempt for my stupidity, would reply that it not only meant but obviously was the word Result, as no other Word containing that sound, and capable of making sense with the context, existed in any language spoken on earth. That less expert mortals should require fuller indications was beyond Sweet’s patience. Therefore, though the whole point of his “Current Shorthand” is that it can express every sound in the language perfectly, vowels as well as consonants, and that your hand has to make no stroke except the easy and current ones with which you write m, n, and u, l, p, and q, scribbling them at whatever angle comes easiest to you, his unfortunate determination to make this remarkable and quite legible script serve also as a Shorthand reduced it in his own practice to the most inscrutable of cryptograms. His true objective was the provision of a full, accurate, legible script for our noble but ill-dressed language; but he was led past that by his contempt for the popular Pitman system of Shorthand, which he called the Pitfall system. The triumph of Pitman was a triumph of business organization: there was a weekly paper to persuade you to learn Pitman: there were cheap textbooks and exercise books and transcripts of speeches for you to copy, and schools where experienced teachers coached you up to the necessary proficiency. Sweet could not organize his market in that fashion. He might as well have been the Sybil who tore up the leaves of prophecy that nobody would attend to. The four and six-penny manual, mostly in his lithographed handwriting, that was never vulgarly advertized, may perhaps some day be taken up by a syndicate and pushed upon the public as The Times pushed the Encyclopaedia Britannica; but until then it will certainly not prevail against Pitman. I have bought three copies of it during my lifetime; and I am informed by the publishers that its cloistered existence is still a steady and healthy one. I actually learned the system two several times; and yet the shorthand in which I am writing these lines is Pitman’s. And the reason is, that my secretary cannot transcribe Sweet, having been perforce taught in the schools of Pitman. Therefore, Sweet railed at Pitman as vainly as Thersites railed at Ajax: his raillery, however it may have eased his soul, gave no popular vogue to Current Shorthand. Pygmalion Higgins is not a portrait of Sweet, to whom the adventure of Eliza Doolittle would have been impossible; still, as will be seen, there are touches of Sweet in the play. With Higgins’s physique and temperament Sweet might have set the Thames on fire. As it was, he impressed himself professionally on Europe to an extent that made his comparative personal obscurity, and the failure of Oxford to do justice to his eminence, a puzzle to foreign specialists in his subject. I do not blame Oxford, because I think Oxford is quite right in demanding a certain social amenity from its nurslings (heaven knows it is not exorbitant in its requirements!); for although I well know how hard it is for a man of genius with a seriously underrated subject to maintain serene and kindly relations with the men who underrate it, and who keep all the best places for less important subjects which they profess without originality and sometimes without much capacity for them, still, if he overwhelms them with wrath and disdain, he cannot expect them to heap honors on him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Of the later generations of phoneticians I know little. Among them towers the Poet Laureate, to whom perhaps Higgins may owe his Miltonic sympathies, though here again I must disclaim all portraiture. But if the play makes the public aware that there are such people as phoneticians, and that they are among the most important people in England at present, it will serve its turn.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>I wish to boast that Pygmalion has been an extremely successful play all over Europe and North America as well as at home. It is so intensely and deliberately didactic, and its subject is esteemed so dry, that I delight in throwing it at the heads of the wiseacres who repeat the parrot cry that art should never be didactic. It goes to prove my contention that art should never be anything else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Finally, and for the encouragement of people troubled with accents that cut them off from all high employment, I may add that the change wrought by Professor Higgins in the flower girl is neither impossible nor uncommon. The modern concierge’s daughter who fulfils her ambition by playing the Queen of Spain in Ruy Blas at the Theatre Francais is only one of many thousands of men and women who have sloughed off their native dialects and acquired a new tongue. But the thing has to be done scientifically, or the last state of the aspirant may be worse than the first. An honest and natural slum dialect is more tolerable than the attempt of a phonetically untaught person to imitate the vulgar dialect of the golf club; and I am sorry to say that in spite of the efforts of our Academy of Dramatic Art, there is still too much sham golfing English on our stage, and too little of the noble English of Forbes Robertson.<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>ACT I</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Covent Garden at 11.15 p.m. Torrents of heavy summer rain. Cab whistles blowing frantically in all directions. Pedestrians running for shelter into the market and under the portico of St. Paul’s Church, where there are already several people, among them a lady and her daughter in evening dress. They are all peering out gloomily at the rain, except one man with his back turned to the rest, who seems wholly preoccupied with a notebook in which he is writing busily.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">The church clock strikes the first quarter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER [in the space between the central pillars, close to the one on her left] I’m getting chilled to the bone. What can Freddy be doing all this time? He’s been gone twenty minutes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER [on her daughter’s right] Not so long. But he ought to have got us a cab by this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">A BYSTANDER [on the lady’s right] He won’t get no cab not until half-past eleven, missus, when they come back after dropping their theatre fares.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. But we must have a cab. We can’t stand here until half-past eleven. It’s too bad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. Well, it ain’t my fault, missus.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. If Freddy had a bit of gumption, he would have got one at the theatre door.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. What could he have done, poor boy?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Other people got cabs. Why couldn’t he?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Freddy rushes in out of the rain from the Southampton Street side, and comes between them closing a dripping umbrella. He is a young man of twenty, in evening dress, very wet around the ankles.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Well, haven’t you got a cab?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. There’s not one to be had for love or money.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Oh, Freddy, there must be one. You can’t have tried.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. It’s too tiresome. Do you expect us to go and get one ourselves?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. I tell you they’re all engaged. The rain was so sudden: nobody was prepared; and everybody had to take a cab. I’ve been to Charing Cross one way and nearly to Ludgate Circus the other; and they were all engaged.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Did you try Trafalgar Square?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. There wasn’t one at Trafalgar Square.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Did you try?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. I tried as far as Charing Cross Station. Did you expect me to walk to Hammersmith?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. You haven’t tried at all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. You really are very helpless, Freddy. Go again; and don’t come back until you have found a cab.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. I shall simply get soaked for nothing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. And what about us? Are we to stay here all night in this draught, with next to nothing on. You selfish pig—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Oh, very well: I’ll go, I’ll go. [He opens his umbrella and dashes off Strandwards, but comes into collision with a flower girl, who is hurrying in for shelter, knocking her basket out of her hands. A blinding flash of lightning, followed instantly by a rattling peal of thunder, orchestrates the incident]</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Nah then, Freddy: look wh’ y’ gowin, deah.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Sorry [he rushes off].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [picking up her scattered flowers and replacing them in the basket] There’s menners f’ yer! Te-oo banches o voylets trod into the mad. [She sits down on the plinth of the column, sorting her flowers, on the lady’s right. She is not at all an attractive person. She is perhaps eighteen, perhaps twenty, hardly older. She wears a little sailor hat of black straw that has long been exposed to the dust and soot of London and has seldom if ever been brushed. Her hair needs washing rather badly: its mousy color can hardly be natural. She wears a shoddy black coat that reaches nearly to her knees and is shaped to her waist. She has a brown skirt with a coarse apron. Her boots are much the worse for wear. She is no doubt as clean as she can afford to be; but compared to the ladies she is very dirty. Her features are no worse than theirs; but their condition leaves something to be desired; and she needs the services of a dentist].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. How do you know that my son’s name is Freddy, pray?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Ow, eez ye-ooa san, is e? Wal, fewd dan y’ de-ooty bawmz a mather should, eed now bettern to spawl a pore gel’s flahrzn than ran awy atbaht pyin. Will ye-oo py me f’them? [Here, with apologies, this desperate attempt to represent her dialect without a phonetic alphabet must be abandoned as unintelligible outside London.]</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Do nothing of the sort, mother. The idea!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Please allow me, Clara. Have you any pennies?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. No. I’ve nothing smaller than sixpence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [hopefully] I can give you change for a tanner, kind lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER [to Clara] Give it to me. [Clara parts reluctantly]. Now [to the girl] This is for your flowers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Thank you kindly, lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Make her give you the change. These things are only a penny a bunch.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Do hold your tongue, Clara. [To the girl]. You can keep the change.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Oh, thank you, lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Now tell me how you know that young gentleman’s name.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. I didn’t.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. I heard you call him by it. Don’t try to deceive me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [protesting] Who’s trying to deceive you? I called him Freddy or Charlie same as you might yourself if you was talking to a stranger and wished to be pleasant. [She sits down beside her basket].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Sixpence thrown away! Really, mamma, you might have spared Freddy that. [She retreats in disgust behind the pillar].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">An elderly gentleman of the amiable military type rushes into shelter, and closes a dripping umbrella. He is in the same plight as Freddy, very wet about the ankles. He is in evening dress, with a light overcoat. He takes the place left vacant by the daughter’s retirement.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. Phew!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER [to the gentleman] Oh, sir, is there any sign of its stopping?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. I’m afraid not. It started worse than ever about two minutes ago. [He goes to the plinth beside the flower girl; puts up his foot on it; and stoops to turn down his trouser ends].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Oh, dear! [She retires sadly and joins her daughter].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [taking advantage of the military gentleman’s proximity to establish friendly relations with him]. If it’s worse it’s a sign it’s nearly over. So cheer up, Captain; and buy a flower off a poor girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. I’m sorry, I haven’t any change.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. I can give you change, Captain,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMEN. For a sovereign? I’ve nothing less.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Garn! Oh do buy a flower off me, Captain. I can change half-a-crown. Take this for tuppence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. Now don’t be troublesome: there’s a good girl. [Trying his pockets] I really haven’t any change—Stop: here’s three hapence, if that’s any use to you [he retreats to the other pillar].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [disappointed, but thinking three halfpence better than nothing] Thank you, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER [to the girl] You be careful: give him a flower for it. There’s a bloke here behind taking down every blessed word you’re saying. [All turn to the man who is taking notes].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [springing up terrified] I ain’t done nothing wrong by speaking to the gentleman. I’ve a right to sell flowers if I keep off the kerb. [Hysterically] I’m a respectable girl: so help me, I never spoke to him except to ask him to buy a flower off me. [General hubbub, mostly sympathetic to the flower girl, but deprecating her excessive sensibility. Cries of Don’t start hollerin. Who’s hurting you? Nobody’s going to touch you. What’s the good of fussing? Steady on. Easy, easy, etc., come from the elderly staid spectators, who pat her comfortingly. Less patient ones bid her shut her head, or ask her roughly what is wrong with her. A remoter group, not knowing what the matter is, crowd in and increase the noise with question and answer: What’s the row? What she do? Where is he? A tec taking her down. What! him? Yes: him over there: Took money off the gentleman, etc. The flower girl, distraught and mobbed, breaks through them to the gentleman, crying mildly] Oh, sir, don’t let him charge me. You dunno what it means to me. They’ll take away my character and drive me on the streets for speaking to gentlemen. They—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [coming forward on her right, the rest crowding after him] There, there, there, there! Who’s hurting you, you silly girl? What do you take me for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. It’s all right: he’s a gentleman: look at his boots. [Explaining to the note taker] She thought you was a copper’s nark, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [with quick interest] What’s a copper’s nark?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER [inept at definition] It’s a—well, it’s a copper’s nark, as you might say. What else would you call it? A sort of informer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [still hysterical] I take my Bible oath I never said a word—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [overbearing but good-humored] Oh, shut up, shut up. Do I look like a policeman?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [far from reassured] Then what did you take down my words for? How do I know whether you took me down right? You just show me what you’ve wrote about me. [The note taker opens his book and holds it steadily under her nose, though the pressure of the mob trying to read it over his shoulders would upset a weaker man]. What’s that? That ain’t proper writing. I can’t read that.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. I can. [Reads, reproducing her pronunciation exactly] “Cheer ap, Keptin; n’ haw ya flahr orf a pore gel.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [much distressed] It’s because I called him Captain. I meant no harm. [To the gentleman] Oh, sir, don’t let him lay a charge agen me for a word like that. You—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. Charge! I make no charge. [To the note taker] Really, sir, if you are a detective, you need not begin protecting me against molestation by young women until I ask you. Anybody could see that the girl meant no harm.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDERS GENERALLY [demonstrating against police espionage] Course they could. What business is it of yours? You mind your own affairs. He wants promotion, he does. Taking down people’s words! Girl never said a word to him. What harm if she did? Nice thing a girl can’t shelter from the rain without being insulted, etc., etc., etc. [She is conducted by the more sympathetic demonstrators back to her plinth, where she resumes her seat and struggles with her emotion].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. He ain’t a tec. He’s a blooming busybody: that’s what he is. I tell you, look at his boots.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [turning on him genially] And how are all your people down at Selsey?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER [suspiciously] Who told you my people come from Selsey?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Never you mind. They did. [To the girl] How do you come to be up so far east? You were born in Lisson Grove.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [appalled] Oh, what harm is there in my leaving Lisson Grove? It wasn’t fit for a pig to live in; and I had to pay four-and-six a week. [In tears] Oh, boo—hoo—oo—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Live where you like; but stop that noise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN [to the girl] Come, come! he can’t touch you: you have a right to live where you please.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">A SARCASTIC BYSTANDER [thrusting himself between the note taker and the gentleman] Park Lane, for instance. I’d like to go into the Housing Question with you, I would.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [subsiding into a brooding melancholy over her basket, and talking very low-spiritedly to herself] I’m a good girl, I am.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC BYSTANDER [not attending to her] Do you know where <i>I</i> come from?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [promptly] Hoxton.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Titterings. Popular interest in the note taker’s performance increases.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC ONE [amazed] Well, who said I didn’t? Bly me! You know everything, you do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [still nursing her sense of injury] Ain’t no call to meddle with me, he ain’t.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER [to her] Of course he ain’t. Don’t you stand it from him. [To the note taker] See here: what call have you to know about people what never offered to meddle with you? Where’s your warrant?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">SEVERAL BYSTANDERS [encouraged by this seeming point of law] Yes: where’s your warrant?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Let him say what he likes. I don’t want to have no truck with him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. You take us for dirt under your feet, don’t you? Catch you taking liberties with a gentleman!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC BYSTANDER. Yes: tell HIM where he come from if you want to go fortune-telling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Cheltenham, Harrow, Cambridge, and India.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. Quite right. [Great laughter. Reaction in the note taker’s favor. Exclamations of He knows all about it. Told him proper. Hear him tell the toff where he come from? etc.]. May I ask, sir, do you do this for your living at a music hall?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. I’ve thought of that. Perhaps I shall some day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The rain has stopped; and the persons on the outside of the crowd begin to drop off.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [resenting the reaction] He’s no gentleman, he ain’t, to interfere with a poor girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER [out of patience, pushing her way rudely to the front and displacing the gentleman, who politely retires to the other side of the pillar] What on earth is Freddy doing? I shall get pneumonia if I stay in this draught any longer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [to himself, hastily making a note of her pronunciation of “monia”] Earlscourt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER [violently] Will you please keep your impertinent remarks to yourself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Did I say that out loud? I didn’t mean to. I beg your pardon. Your mother’s Epsom, unmistakeably.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER [advancing between her daughter and the note taker] How very curious! I was brought up in Largelady Park, near Epsom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [uproariously amused] Ha! ha! What a devil of a name! Excuse me. [To the daughter] You want a cab, do you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. Don’t dare speak to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. Oh, please, please Clara. [Her daughter repudiates her with an angry shrug and retires haughtily.] We should be so grateful to you, sir, if you found us a cab. [The note taker produces a whistle]. Oh, thank you. [She joins her daughter]. The note taker blows a piercing blast.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC BYSTANDER. There! I knowed he was a plain-clothes copper.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. That ain’t a police whistle: that’s a sporting whistle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [still preoccupied with her wounded feelings] He’s no right to take away my character. My character is the same to me as any lady’s.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. I don’t know whether you’ve noticed it; but the rain stopped about two minutes ago.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE BYSTANDER. So it has. Why didn’t you say so before? and us losing our time listening to your silliness. [He walks off towards the Strand].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC BYSTANDER. I can tell where you come from. You come from Anwell. Go back there.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [helpfully] <i>H</i>anwell.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE SARCASTIC BYSTANDER [affecting great distinction of speech] Thenk you, teacher. Haw haw! So long [he touches his hat with mock respect and strolls off].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Frightening people like that! How would he like it himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE MOTHER. It’s quite fine now, Clara. We can walk to a motor bus. Come. [She gathers her skirts above her ankles and hurries off towards the Strand].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE DAUGHTER. But the cab—[her mother is out of hearing]. Oh, how tiresome! [She follows angrily].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">All the rest have gone except the note taker, the gentleman, and the flower girl, who sits arranging her basket, and still pitying herself in murmurs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Poor girl! Hard enough for her to live without being worrited and chivied.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN [returning to his former place on the note taker’s left] How do you do it, if I may ask?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Simply phonetics. The science of speech. That’s my profession; also my hobby. Happy is the man who can make a living by his hobby! You can spot an Irishman or a Yorkshireman by his brogue. I can place any man within six miles. I can place him within two miles in London. Sometimes within two streets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Ought to be ashamed of himself, unmanly coward!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. But is there a living in that?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Oh yes. Quite a fat one. This is an age of upstarts. Men begin in Kentish Town with 80 pounds a year, and end in Park Lane with a hundred thousand. They want to drop Kentish Town; but they give themselves away every time they open their mouths. Now I can teach them—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Let him mind his own business and leave a poor girl—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [explosively] Woman: cease this detestable boohooing instantly; or else seek the shelter of some other place of worship.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [with feeble defiance] I’ve a right to be here if I like, same as you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. A woman who utters such depressing and disgusting sounds has no right to be anywhere—no right to live. Remember that you are a human being with a soul and the divine gift of articulate speech: that your native language is the language of Shakespear and Milton and The Bible; and don’t sit there crooning like a bilious pigeon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [quite overwhelmed, and looking up at him in mingled wonder and deprecation without daring to raise her head] Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—oo!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [whipping out his book] Heavens! what a sound! [He writes; then holds out the book and reads, reproducing her vowels exactly] Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—ow—oo!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [tickled by the performance, and laughing in spite of herself] Garn!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. You see this creature with her kerbstone English: the English that will keep her in the gutter to the end of her days. Well, sir, in three months I could pass that girl off as a duchess at an ambassador’s garden party. I could even get her a place as lady’s maid or shop assistant, which requires better English. That’s the sort of thing I do for commercial millionaires. And on the profits of it I do genuine scientific work in phonetics, and a little as a poet on Miltonic lines.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. I am myself a student of Indian dialects; and—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER [eagerly] Are you? Do you know Colonel Pickering, the author of Spoken Sanscrit?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE GENTLEMAN. I am Colonel Pickering. Who are you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE NOTE TAKER. Henry Higgins, author of Higgins’s Universal Alphabet.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [with enthusiasm] I came from India to meet you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I was going to India to meet you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Where do you live?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. 27A Wimpole Street. Come and see me tomorrow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I’m at the Carlton. Come with me now and let’s have a jaw over some supper.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Right you are.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [to Pickering, as he passes her] Buy a flower, kind gentleman. I’m short for my lodging.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I really haven’t any change. I’m sorry [he goes away].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [shocked at girl’s mendacity] Liar. You said you could change half-a-crown.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [rising in desperation] You ought to be stuffed with nails, you ought. [Flinging the basket at his feet] Take the whole blooming basket for sixpence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The church clock strikes the second quarter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [hearing in it the voice of God, rebuking him for his Pharisaic want of charity to the poor girl] A reminder. [He raises his hat solemnly; then throws a handful of money into the basket and follows Pickering].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [picking up a half-crown] Ah—ow—ooh! [Picking up a couple of florins] Aaah—ow—ooh! [Picking up several coins] Aaaaaah—ow—ooh! [Picking up a half-sovereign] Aasaaaaaaaaah—ow—ooh!!!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [springing out of a taxicab] Got one at last. Hallo! [To the girl] Where are the two ladies that were here?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. They walked to the bus when the rain stopped.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. And left me with a cab on my hands. Damnation!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [with grandeur] Never you mind, young man. I’m going home in a taxi. [She sails off to the cab. The driver puts his hand behind him and holds the door firmly shut against her. Quite understanding his mistrust, she shows him her handful of money]. Eightpence ain’t no object to me, Charlie. [He grins and opens the door]. Angel Court, Drury Lane, round the corner of Micklejohn’s oil shop. Let’s see how fast you can make her hop it. [She gets in and pulls the door to with a slam as the taxicab starts].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Well, I’m dashed!<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>ACT II</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Next day at 11 a.m. Higgins’s laboratory in Wimpole Street. It is a room on the first floor, looking on the street, and was meant for the drawing-room. The double doors are in the middle of the back hall; and persons entering find in the corner to their right two tall file cabinets at right angles to one another against the walls. In this corner stands a flat writing-table, on which are a phonograph, a laryngoscope, a row of tiny organ pipes with a bellows, a set of lamp chimneys for singing flames with burners attached to a gas plug in the wall by an indiarubber tube, several tuning-forks of different sizes, a life-size image of half a human head, showing in section the vocal organs, and a box containing a supply of wax cylinders for the phonograph.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Further down the room, on the same side, is a fireplace, with a comfortable leather-covered easy-chair at the side of the hearth nearest the door, and a coal-scuttle. There is a clock on the mantelpiece. Between the fireplace and the phonograph table is a stand for newspapers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">On the other side of the central door, to the left of the visitor, is a cabinet of shallow drawers. On it is a telephone and the telephone directory. The corner beyond, and most of the side wall, is occupied by a grand piano, with the keyboard at the end furthest from the door, and a bench for the player extending the full length of the keyboard. On the piano is a dessert dish heaped with fruit and sweets, mostly chocolates.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">The middle of the room is clear. Besides the easy chair, the piano bench, and two chairs at the phonograph table, there is one stray chair. It stands near the fireplace. On the walls, engravings; mostly Piranesis and mezzotint portraits. No paintings.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Pickering is seated at the table, putting down some cards and a tuning-fork which he has been using. Higgins is standing up near him, closing two or three file drawers which are hanging out. He appears in the morning light as a robust, vital, appetizing sort of man of forty or thereabouts, dressed in a professional-looking black frock-coat with a white linen collar and black silk tie. He is of the energetic, scientific type, heartily, even violently interested in everything that can be studied as a scientific subject, and careless about himself and other people, including their feelings. He is, in fact, but for his years and size, rather like a very impetuous baby “taking notice” eagerly and loudly, and requiring almost as much watching to keep him out of unintended mischief. His manner varies from genial bullying when he is in a good humor to stormy petulance when anything goes wrong; but he is so entirely frank and void of malice that he remains likeable even in his least reasonable moments.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [as he shuts the last drawer] Well, I think that’s the whole show.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. It’s really amazing. I haven’t taken half of it in, you know.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Would you like to go over any of it again?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [rising and coming to the fireplace, where he plants himself with his back to the fire] No, thank you; not now. I’m quite done up for this morning.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [following him, and standing beside him on his left] Tired of listening to sounds?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Yes. It’s a fearful strain. I rather fancied myself because I can pronounce twenty-four distinct vowel sounds; but your hundred and thirty beat me. I can’t hear a bit of difference between most of them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [chuckling, and going over to the piano to eat sweets] Oh, that comes with practice. You hear no difference at first; but you keep on listening, and presently you find they’re all as different as A from B. [Mrs. Pearce looks in: she is Higgins’s housekeeper] What’s the matter?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [hesitating, evidently perplexed] A young woman wants to see you, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. A young woman! What does she want?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Well, sir, she says you’ll be glad to see her when you know what she’s come about. She’s quite a common girl, sir. Very common indeed. I should have sent her away, only I thought perhaps you wanted her to talk into your machines. I hope I’ve not done wrong; but really you see such queer people sometimes—you’ll excuse me, I’m sure, sir—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, that’s all right, Mrs. Pearce. Has she an interesting accent?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Oh, something dreadful, sir, really. I don’t know how you can take an interest in it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [to Pickering] Let’s have her up. Show her up, Mrs. Pearce [he rushes across to his working table and picks out a cylinder to use on the phonograph].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [only half resigned to it] Very well, sir. It’s for you to say. [She goes downstairs].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. This is rather a bit of luck. I’ll show you how I make records. We’ll set her talking; and I’ll take it down first in Bell’s visible Speech; then in broad Romic; and then we’ll get her on the phonograph so that you can turn her on as often as you like with the written transcript before you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [returning] This is the young woman, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The flower girl enters in state. She has a hat with three ostrich feathers, orange, sky-blue, and red. She has a nearly clean apron, and the shoddy coat has been tidied a little. The pathos of this deplorable figure, with its innocent vanity and consequential air, touches Pickering, who has already straightened himself in the presence of Mrs. Pearce. But as to Higgins, the only distinction he makes between men and women is that when he is neither bullying nor exclaiming to the heavens against some featherweight cross, he coaxes women as a child coaxes its nurse when it wants to get anything out of her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [brusquely, recognizing her with unconcealed disappointment, and at once, baby-like, making an intolerable grievance of it] Why, this is the girl I jotted down last night. She’s no use: I’ve got all the records I want of the Lisson Grove lingo; and I’m not going to waste another cylinder on it. [To the girl] Be off with you: I don’t want you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Don’t you be so saucy. You ain’t heard what I come for yet. [To Mrs. Pearce, who is waiting at the door for further instruction] Did you tell him I come in a taxi?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Nonsense, girl! what do you think a gentleman like Mr. Higgins cares what you came in?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Oh, we are proud! He ain’t above giving lessons, not him: I heard him say so. Well, I ain’t come here to ask for any compliment; and if my money’s not good enough I can go elsewhere.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Good enough for what?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Good enough for ye—oo. Now you know, don’t you? I’m come to have lessons, I am. And to pay for em too: make no mistake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [stupent] WELL!!! [Recovering his breath with a gasp] What do you expect me to say to you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Well, if you was a gentleman, you might ask me to sit down, I think. Don’t I tell you I’m bringing you business?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Pickering: shall we ask this baggage to sit down or shall we throw her out of the window?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [running away in terror to the piano, where she turns at bay] Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—ow—oo! [Wounded and whimpering] I won’t be called a baggage when I’ve offered to pay like any lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Motionless, the two men stare at her from the other side of the room, amazed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [gently] What is it you want, my girl?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. I want to be a lady in a flower shop stead of selling at the corner of Tottenham Court Road. But they won’t take me unless I can talk more genteel. He said he could teach me. Well, here I am ready to pay him—not asking any favor—and he treats me as if I was dirt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. How can you be such a foolish ignorant girl as to think you could afford to pay Mr. Higgins?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Why shouldn’t I? I know what lessons cost as well as you do; and I’m ready to pay.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. How much?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL [coming back to him, triumphant] Now you’re talking! I thought you’d come off it when you saw a chance of getting back a bit of what you chucked at me last night. [Confidentially] You’d had a drop in, hadn’t you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [peremptorily] Sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Oh, if you’re going to make a compliment of it—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [thundering at her] Sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [severely] Sit down, girl. Do as you’re told. [She places the stray chair near the hearthrug between Higgins and Pickering, and stands behind it waiting for the girl to sit down].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—oo! [She stands, half rebellious, half bewildered].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [very courteous] Won’t you sit down?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [coyly] Don’t mind if I do. [She sits down. Pickering returns to the hearthrug].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What’s your name?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE FLOWER GIRL. Liza Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [declaiming gravely] Eliza, Elizabeth, Betsy and Bess, They went to the woods to get a bird’s nes’:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. They found a nest with four eggs in it:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. They took one apiece, and left three in it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">They laugh heartily at their own wit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, don’t be silly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. You mustn’t speak to the gentleman like that.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Well, why won’t he speak sensible to me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Come back to business. How much do you propose to pay me for the lessons?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, I know what’s right. A lady friend of mine gets French lessons for eighteenpence an hour from a real French gentleman. Well, you wouldn’t have the face to ask me the same for teaching me my own language as you would for French; so I won’t give more than a shilling. Take it or leave it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [walking up and down the room, rattling his keys and his cash in his pockets] You know, Pickering, if you consider a shilling, not as a simple shilling, but as a percentage of this girl’s income, it works out as fully equivalent to sixty or seventy guineas from a millionaire.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. How so?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Figure it out. A millionaire has about 150 pounds a day. She earns about half-a-crown.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [haughtily] Who told you I only—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [continuing] She offers me two-fifths of her day’s income for a lesson. Two-fifths of a millionaire’s income for a day would be somewhere about 60 pounds. It’s handsome. By George, it’s enormous! it’s the biggest offer I ever had.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [rising, terrified] Sixty pounds! What are you talking about? I never offered you sixty pounds. Where would I get—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Hold your tongue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [weeping] But I ain’t got sixty pounds. Oh—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Don’t cry, you silly girl. Sit down. Nobody is going to touch your money.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Somebody is going to touch you, with a broomstick, if you don’t stop snivelling. Sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [obeying slowly] Ah—ah—ah—ow—oo—o! One would think you was my father.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. If I decide to teach you, I’ll be worse than two fathers to you. Here [he offers her his silk handkerchief]!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What’s this for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. To wipe your eyes. To wipe any part of your face that feels moist. Remember: that’s your handkerchief; and that’s your sleeve. Don’t mistake the one for the other if you wish to become a lady in a shop.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Liza, utterly bewildered, stares helplessly at him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. It’s no use talking to her like that, Mr. Higgins: she doesn’t understand you. Besides, you’re quite wrong: she doesn’t do it that way at all [she takes the handkerchief].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [snatching it] Here! You give me that handkerchief. He give it to me, not to you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [laughing] He did. I think it must be regarded as her property, Mrs. Pearce.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [resigning herself] Serve you right, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Higgins: I’m interested. What about the ambassador’s garden party? I’ll say you’re the greatest teacher alive if you make that good. I’ll bet you all the expenses of the experiment you can’t do it. And I’ll pay for the lessons.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, you are real good. Thank you, Captain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [tempted, looking at her] It’s almost irresistible. She’s so deliciously low—so horribly dirty—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [protesting extremely] Ah—ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—oooo!!! I ain’t dirty: I washed my face and hands afore I come, I did.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. You’re certainly not going to turn her head with flattery, Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [uneasy] Oh, don’t say that, sir: there’s more ways than one of turning a girl’s head; and nobody can do it better than Mr. Higgins, though he may not always mean it. I do hope, sir, you won’t encourage him to do anything foolish.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [becoming excited as the idea grows on him] What is life but a series of inspired follies? The difficulty is to find them to do. Never lose a chance: it doesn’t come every day. I shall make a duchess of this draggletailed guttersnipe.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [strongly deprecating this view of her] Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—oo!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [carried away] Yes: in six months—in three if she has a good ear and a quick tongue—I’ll take her anywhere and pass her off as anything. We’ll start today: now! this moment! Take her away and clean her, Mrs. Pearce. Monkey Brand, if it won’t come off any other way. Is there a good fire in the kitchen?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [protesting]. Yes; but—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [storming on] Take all her clothes off and burn them. Ring up Whiteley or somebody for new ones. Wrap her up in brown paper till they come.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You’re no gentleman, you’re not, to talk of such things. I’m a good girl, I am; and I know what the like of you are, I do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. We want none of your Lisson Grove prudery here, young woman. You’ve got to learn to behave like a duchess. Take her away, Mrs. Pearce. If she gives you any trouble wallop her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [springing up and running between Pickering and Mrs. Pearce for protection] No! I’ll call the police, I will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. But I’ve no place to put her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Put her in the dustbin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Ah—ah—ah—ow—ow—oo!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh come, Higgins! be reasonable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [resolutely] You must be reasonable, Mr. Higgins: really you must. You can’t walk over everybody like this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins, thus scolded, subsides. The hurricane is succeeded by a zephyr of amiable surprise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [with professional exquisiteness of modulation] I walk over everybody! My dear Mrs. Pearce, my dear Pickering, I never had the slightest intention of walking over anyone. All I propose is that we should be kind to this poor girl. We must help her to prepare and fit herself for her new station in life. If I did not express myself clearly it was because I did not wish to hurt her delicacy, or yours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Liza, reassured, steals back to her chair.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [to Pickering] Well, did you ever hear anything like that, sir?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [laughing heartily] Never, Mrs. Pearce: never.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [patiently] What’s the matter?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Well, the matter is, sir, that you can’t take a girl up like that as if you were picking up a pebble on the beach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Why not?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Why not! But you don’t know anything about her. What about her parents? She may be married.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Garn!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. There! As the girl very properly says, Garn! Married indeed! Don’t you know that a woman of that class looks a worn out drudge of fifty a year after she’s married.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Who’d marry me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [suddenly resorting to the most thrillingly beautiful low tones in his best elocutionary style] By George, Eliza, the streets will be strewn with the bodies of men shooting themselves for your sake before I’ve done with you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Nonsense, sir. You mustn’t talk like that to her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [rising and squaring herself determinedly] I’m going away. He’s off his chump, he is. I don’t want no balmies teaching me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [wounded in his tenderest point by her insensibility to his elocution] Oh, indeed! I’m mad, am I? Very well, Mrs. Pearce: you needn’t order the new clothes for her. Throw her out.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [whimpering] Nah—ow. You got no right to touch me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. You see now what comes of being saucy. [Indicating the door] This way, please.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [almost in tears] I didn’t want no clothes. I wouldn’t have taken them [she throws away the handkerchief]. I can buy my own clothes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [deftly retrieving the handkerchief and intercepting her on her reluctant way to the door] You’re an ungrateful wicked girl. This is my return for offering to take you out of the gutter and dress you beautifully and make a lady of you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Stop, Mr. Higgins. I won’t allow it. It’s you that are wicked. Go home to your parents, girl; and tell them to take better care of you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I ain’t got no parents. They told me I was big enough to earn my own living and turned me out.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Where’s your mother?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I ain’t got no mother. Her that turned me out was my sixth stepmother. But I done without them. And I’m a good girl, I am.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Very well, then, what on earth is all this fuss about? The girl doesn’t belong to anybody—is no use to anybody but me. [He goes to Mrs. Pearce and begins coaxing]. You can adopt her, Mrs. Pearce: I’m sure a daughter would be a great amusement to you. Now don’t make any more fuss. Take her downstairs; and—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. But what’s to become of her? Is she to be paid anything? Do be sensible, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, pay her whatever is necessary: put it down in the housekeeping book. [Impatiently] What on earth will she want with money? She’ll have her food and her clothes. She’ll only drink if you give her money.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [turning on him] Oh you are a brute. It’s a lie: nobody ever saw the sign of liquor on me. [She goes back to her chair and plants herself there defiantly].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [in good-humored remonstrance] Does it occur to you, Higgins, that the girl has some feelings?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [looking critically at her] Oh no, I don’t think so. Not any feelings that we need bother about. [Cheerily] Have you, Eliza?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I got my feelings same as anyone else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [to Pickering, reflectively] You see the difficulty?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Eh? What difficulty?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. To get her to talk grammar. The mere pronunciation is easy enough.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I don’t want to talk grammar. I want to talk like a lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Will you please keep to the point, Mr. Higgins. I want to know on what terms the girl is to be here. Is she to have any wages? And what is to become of her when you’ve finished your teaching? You must look ahead a little.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [impatiently] What’s to become of her if I leave her in the gutter? Tell me that, Mrs. Pearce.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. That’s her own business, not yours, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, when I’ve done with her, we can throw her back into the gutter; and then it will be her own business again; so that’s all right.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, you’ve no feeling heart in you: you don’t care for nothing but yourself [she rises and takes the floor resolutely]. Here! I’ve had enough of this. I’m going [making for the door]. You ought to be ashamed of yourself, you ought.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [snatching a chocolate cream from the piano, his eyes suddenly beginning to twinkle with mischief] Have some chocolates, Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [halting, tempted] How do I know what might be in them? I’ve heard of girls being drugged by the like of you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins whips out his penknife; cuts a chocolate in two; puts one half into his mouth and bolts it; and offers her the other half.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Pledge of good faith, Eliza. I eat one half you eat the other.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">[Liza opens her mouth to retort: he pops the half chocolate into it]. You shall have boxes of them, barrels of them, every day. You shall live on them. Eh?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [who has disposed of the chocolate after being nearly choked by it] I wouldn’t have ate it, only I’m too ladylike to take it out of my mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Listen, Eliza. I think you said you came in a taxi.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Well, what if I did? I’ve as good a right to take a taxi as anyone else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You have, Eliza; and in future you shall have as many taxis as you want. You shall go up and down and round the town in a taxi every day. Think of that, Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Mr. Higgins: you’re tempting the girl. It’s not right. She should think of the future.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. At her age! Nonsense! Time enough to think of the future when you haven’t any future to think of. No, Eliza: do as this lady does: think of other people’s futures; but never think of your own. Think of chocolates, and taxis, and gold, and diamonds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No: I don’t want no gold and no diamonds. I’m a good girl, I am. [She sits down again, with an attempt at dignity].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You shall remain so, Eliza, under the care of Mrs. Pearce. And you shall marry an officer in the Guards, with a beautiful moustache: the son of a marquis, who will disinherit him for marrying you, but will relent when he sees your beauty and goodness—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Excuse me, Higgins; but I really must interfere. Mrs. Pearce is quite right. If this girl is to put herself in your hands for six months for an experiment in teaching, she must understand thoroughly what she’s doing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. How can she? She’s incapable of understanding anything. Besides, do any of us understand what we are doing? If we did, would we ever do it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Very clever, Higgins; but not sound sense. [To Eliza] Miss Doolittle—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [overwhelmed] Ah—ah—ow—oo!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. There! That’s all you get out of Eliza. Ah—ah—ow—oo! No use explaining. As a military man you ought to know that. Give her her orders: that’s what she wants. Eliza: you are to live here for the next six months, learning how to speak beautifully, like a lady in a florist’s shop. If you’re good and do whatever you’re told, you shall sleep in a proper bedroom, and have lots to eat, and money to buy chocolates and take rides in taxis. If you’re naughty and idle you will sleep in the back kitchen among the black beetles, and be walloped by Mrs. Pearce with a broomstick. At the end of six months you shall go to Buckingham Palace in a carriage, beautifully dressed. If the King finds out you’re not a lady, you will be taken by the police to the Tower of London, where your head will be cut off as a warning to other presumptuous flower girls. If you are not found out, you shall have a present of seven-and-sixpence to start life with as a lady in a shop. If you refuse this offer you will be a most ungrateful and wicked girl; and the angels will weep for you. [To Pickering] Now are you satisfied, Pickering? [To Mrs. Pearce] Can I put it more plainly and fairly, Mrs. Pearce?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [patiently] I think you’d better let me speak to the girl properly in private. I don’t know that I can take charge of her or consent to the arrangement at all. Of course I know you don’t mean her any harm; but when you get what you call interested in people’s accents, you never think or care what may happen to them or you. Come with me, Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. That’s all right. Thank you, Mrs. Pearce. Bundle her off to the bath-room.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [rising reluctantly and suspiciously] You’re a great bully, you are. I won’t stay here if I don’t like. I won’t let nobody wallop me. I never asked to go to Bucknam Palace, I didn’t. I was never in trouble with the police, not me. I’m a good girl—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Don’t answer back, girl. You don’t understand the gentleman. Come with me. [She leads the way to the door, and holds it open for Eliza].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [as she goes out] Well, what I say is right. I won’t go near the king, not if I’m going to have my head cut off. If I’d known what I was letting myself in for, I wouldn’t have come here. I always been a good girl; and I never offered to say a word to him; and I don’t owe him nothing; and I don’t care; and I won’t be put upon; and I have my feelings the same as anyone else—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Pearce shuts the door; and Eliza’s plaints are no longer audible. Pickering comes from the hearth to the chair and sits astride it with his arms on the back.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Excuse the straight question, Higgins. Are you a man of good character where women are concerned?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [moodily] Have you ever met a man of good character where women are concerned?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Yes: very frequently.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [dogmatically, lifting himself on his hands to the level of the piano, and sitting on it with a bounce] Well, I haven’t. I find that the moment I let a woman make friends with me, she becomes jealous, exacting, suspicious, and a damned nuisance. I find that the moment I let myself make friends with a woman, I become selfish and tyrannical. Women upset everything. When you let them into your life, you find that the woman is driving at one thing and you’re driving at another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. At what, for example?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [coming off the piano restlessly] Oh, Lord knows! I suppose the woman wants to live her own life; and the man wants to live his; and each tries to drag the other on to the wrong track. One wants to go north and the other south; and the result is that both have to go east, though they both hate the east wind. [He sits down on the bench at the keyboard]. So here I am, a confirmed old bachelor, and likely to remain so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [rising and standing over him gravely] Come, Higgins! You know what I mean. If I’m to be in this business I shall feel responsible for that girl. I hope it’s understood that no advantage is to be taken of her position.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What! That thing! Sacred, I assure you. [Rising to explain] You see, she’ll be a pupil; and teaching would be impossible unless pupils were sacred. I’ve taught scores of American millionairesses how to speak English: the best looking women in the world. I’m seasoned. They might as well be blocks of wood. I might as well be a block of wood. It’s—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Pearce opens the door. She has Eliza’s hat in her hand. Pickering retires to the easy-chair at the hearth and sits down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [eagerly] Well, Mrs. Pearce: is it all right?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [at the door] I just wish to trouble you with a word, if I may, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes, certainly. Come in. [She comes forward]. Don’t burn that, Mrs. Pearce. I’ll keep it as a curiosity. [He takes the hat].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Handle it carefully, sir, please. I had to promise her not to burn it; but I had better put it in the oven for a while.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [putting it down hastily on the piano] Oh! thank you. Well, what have you to say to me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Am I in the way?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Not at all, sir. Mr. Higgins: will you please be very particular what you say before the girl?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [sternly] Of course. I’m always particular about what I say. Why do you say this to me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [unmoved] No, sir: you’re not at all particular when you’ve mislaid anything or when you get a little impatient. Now it doesn’t matter before me: I’m used to it. But you really must not swear before the girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [indignantly] I swear! [Most emphatically] I never swear. I detest the habit. What the devil do you mean?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [stolidly] That’s what I mean, sir. You swear a great deal too much. I don’t mind your damning and blasting, and what the devil and where the devil and who the devil—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Really! Mrs. Pearce: this language from your lips!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [not to be put off]—but there is a certain word I must ask you not to use. The girl has just used it herself because the bath was too hot. It begins with the same letter as bath. She knows no better: she learnt it at her mother’s knee. But she must not hear it from your lips.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [loftily] I cannot charge myself with having ever uttered it, Mrs. Pearce. [She looks at him steadfastly. He adds, hiding an uneasy conscience with a judicial air] Except perhaps in a moment of extreme and justifiable excitement.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Only this morning, sir, you applied it to your boots, to the butter, and to the brown bread.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, that! Mere alliteration, Mrs. Pearce, natural to a poet.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Well, sir, whatever you choose to call it, I beg you not to let the girl hear you repeat it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, very well, very well. Is that all?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. No, sir. We shall have to be very particular with this girl as to personal cleanliness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Certainly. Quite right. Most important.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. I mean not to be slovenly about her dress or untidy in leaving things about.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [going to her solemnly] Just so. I intended to call your attention to that [He passes on to Pickering, who is enjoying the conversation immensely]. It is these little things that matter, Pickering. Take care of the pence and the pounds will take care of themselves is as true of personal habits as of money. [He comes to anchor on the hearthrug, with the air of a man in an unassailable position].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Yes, sir. Then might I ask you not to come down to breakfast in your dressing-gown, or at any rate not to use it as a napkin to the extent you do, sir. And if you would be so good as not to eat everything off the same plate, and to remember not to put the porridge saucepan out of your hand on the clean tablecloth, it would be a better example to the girl. You know you nearly choked yourself with a fishbone in the jam only last week.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [routed from the hearthrug and drifting back to the piano] I may do these things sometimes in absence of mind; but surely I don’t do them habitually. [Angrily] By the way: my dressing-gown smells most damnably of benzine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. No doubt it does, Mr. Higgins. But if you will wipe your fingers—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [yelling] Oh very well, very well: I’ll wipe them in my hair in future.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. I hope you’re not offended, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [shocked at finding himself thought capable of an unamiable sentiment] Not at all, not at all. You’re quite right, Mrs. Pearce: I shall be particularly careful before the girl. Is that all?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. No, sir. Might she use some of those Japanese dresses you brought from abroad? I really can’t put her back into her old things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Certainly. Anything you like. Is that all?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Thank you, sir. That’s all. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You know, Pickering, that woman has the most extraordinary ideas about me. Here I am, a shy, diffident sort of man. I’ve never been able to feel really grown-up and tremendous, like other chaps. And yet she’s firmly persuaded that I’m an arbitrary overbearing bossing kind of person. I can’t account for it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Pearce returns.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. If you please, sir, the trouble’s beginning already. There’s a dustman downstairs, Alfred Doolittle, wants to see you. He says you have his daughter here.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [rising] Phew! I say! [He retreats to the hearthrug].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [promptly] Send the blackguard up.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Oh, very well, sir. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. He may not be a blackguard, Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Nonsense. Of course he’s a blackguard.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Whether he is or not, I’m afraid we shall have some trouble with him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [confidently] Oh no: I think not. If there’s any trouble he shall have it with me, not I with him. And we are sure to get something interesting out of him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. About the girl?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. No. I mean his dialect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [at the door] Doolittle, sir. [She admits Doolittle and retires].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Alfred Doolittle is an elderly but vigorous dustman, clad in the costume of his profession, including a hat with a back brim covering his neck and shoulders. He has well marked and rather interesting features, and seems equally free from fear and conscience. He has a remarkably expressive voice, the result of a habit of giving vent to his feelings without reserve. His present pose is that of wounded honor and stern resolution.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [at the door, uncertain which of the two gentlemen is his man] Professor Higgins?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Here. Good morning. Sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Morning, Governor. [He sits down magisterially] I come about a very serious matter, Governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [to Pickering] Brought up in Hounslow. Mother Welsh, I should think. [Doolittle opens his mouth, amazed. Higgins continues] What do you want, Doolittle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [menacingly] I want my daughter: that’s what I want. See?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Of course you do. You’re her father, aren’t you? You don’t suppose anyone else wants her, do you? I’m glad to see you have some spark of family feeling left. She’s upstairs. Take her away at once.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [rising, fearfully taken aback] What!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Take her away. Do you suppose I’m going to keep your daughter for you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [remonstrating] Now, now, look here, Governor. Is this reasonable? Is it fair to take advantage of a man like this? The girl belongs to me. You got her. Where do I come in? [He sits down again].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Your daughter had the audacity to come to my house and ask me to teach her how to speak properly so that she could get a place in a flower-shop. This gentleman and my housekeeper have been here all the time. [Bullying him] How dare you come here and attempt to blackmail me? You sent her here on purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [protesting] No, Governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You must have. How else could you possibly know that she is here?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Don’t take a man up like that, Governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. The police shall take you up. This is a plant—a plot to extort money by threats. I shall telephone for the police [he goes resolutely to the telephone and opens the directory].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Have I asked you for a brass farthing? I leave it to the gentleman here: have I said a word about money?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [throwing the book aside and marching down on Doolittle with a poser] What else did you come for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [sweetly] Well, what would a man come for? Be human, governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [disarmed] Alfred: did you put her up to it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. So help me, Governor, I never did. I take my Bible oath I ain’t seen the girl these two months past.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Then how did you know she was here?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [“most musical, most melancholy”] I’ll tell you, Governor, if you’ll only let me get a word in. I’m willing to tell you. I’m wanting to tell you. I’m waiting to tell you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Pickering: this chap has a certain natural gift of rhetoric. Observe the rhythm of his native woodnotes wild. “I’m willing to tell you: I’m wanting to tell you: I’m waiting to tell you.” Sentimental rhetoric! That’s the Welsh strain in him. It also accounts for his mendacity and dishonesty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh, PLEASE, Higgins: I’m west country myself. [To Doolittle] How did you know the girl was here if you didn’t send her?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. It was like this, Governor. The girl took a boy in the taxi to give him a jaunt. Son of her landlady, he is. He hung about on the chance of her giving him another ride home. Well, she sent him back for her luggage when she heard you was willing for her to stop here. I met the boy at the corner of Long Acre and Endell Street.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Public house. Yes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. The poor man’s club, Governor: why shouldn’t I?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Do let him tell his story, Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. He told me what was up. And I ask you, what was my feelings and my duty as a father? I says to the boy, “You bring me the luggage,” I says—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Why didn’t you go for it yourself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Landlady wouldn’t have trusted me with it, Governor. She’s that kind of woman: you know. I had to give the boy a penny afore he trusted me with it, the little swine. I brought it to her just to oblige you like, and make myself agreeable. That’s all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. How much luggage?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Musical instrument, Governor. A few pictures, a trifle of jewelry, and a bird-cage. She said she didn’t want no clothes. What was I to think from that, Governor? I ask you as a parent what was I to think?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. So you came to rescue her from worse than death, eh?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [appreciatively: relieved at being understood] Just so, Governor. That’s right.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. But why did you bring her luggage if you intended to take her away?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Have I said a word about taking her away? Have I now?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [determinedly] You’re going to take her away, double quick. [He crosses to the hearth and rings the bell].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [rising] No, Governor. Don’t say that. I’m not the man to stand in my girl’s light. Here’s a career opening for her, as you might say; and—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Pearce opens the door and awaits orders.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Mrs. Pearce: this is Eliza’s father. He has come to take her away. Give her to him. [He goes back to the piano, with an air of washing his hands of the whole affair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. No. This is a misunderstanding. Listen here—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. He can’t take her away, Mr. Higgins: how can he? You told me to burn her clothes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. That’s right. I can’t carry the girl through the streets like a blooming monkey, can I? I put it to you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You have put it to me that you want your daughter. Take your daughter. If she has no clothes go out and buy her some.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [desperate] Where’s the clothes she come in? Did I burn them or did your missus here?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. I am the housekeeper, if you please. I have sent for some clothes for your girl. When they come you can take her away. You can wait in the kitchen. This way, please.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Doolittle, much troubled, accompanies her to the door; then hesitates; finally turns confidentially to Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Listen here, Governor. You and me is men of the world, ain’t we?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh! Men of the world, are we? You’d better go, Mrs. Pearce.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. I think so, indeed, sir. [She goes, with dignity].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. The floor is yours, Mr. Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [to Pickering] I thank you, Governor. [To Higgins, who takes refuge on the piano bench, a little overwhelmed by the proximity of his visitor; for Doolittle has a professional flavor of dust about him]. Well, the truth is, I’ve taken a sort of fancy to you, Governor; and if you want the girl, I’m not so set on having her back home again but what I might be open to an arrangement. Regarded in the light of a young woman, she’s a fine handsome girl. As a daughter she’s not worth her keep; and so I tell you straight. All I ask is my rights as a father; and you’re the last man alive to expect me to let her go for nothing; for I can see you’re one of the straight sort, Governor. Well, what’s a five pound note to you? And what’s Eliza to me? [He returns to his chair and sits down judicially].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I think you ought to know, Doolittle, that Mr. Higgins’s intentions are entirely honorable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Course they are, Governor. If I thought they wasn’t, I’d ask fifty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [revolted] Do you mean to say, you callous rascal, that you would sell your daughter for 50 pounds?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Not in a general way I wouldn’t; but to oblige a gentleman like you I’d do a good deal, I do assure you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Have you no morals, man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [unabashed] Can’t afford them, Governor. Neither could you if you was as poor as me. Not that I mean any harm, you know. But if Liza is going to have a bit out of this, why not me too?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [troubled] I don’t know what to do, Pickering. There can be no question that as a matter of morals it’s a positive crime to give this chap a farthing. And yet I feel a sort of rough justice in his claim.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. That’s it, Governor. That’s all I say. A father’s heart, as it were.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Well, I know the feeling; but really it seems hardly right—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Don’t say that, Governor. Don’t look at it that way. What am I, Governors both? I ask you, what am I? I’m one of the undeserving poor: that’s what I am. Think of what that means to a man. It means that he’s up agen middle class morality all the time. If there’s anything going, and I put in for a bit of it, it’s always the same story: “You’re undeserving; so you can’t have it.” But my needs is as great as the most deserving widow’s that ever got money out of six different charities in one week for the death of the same husband. I don’t need less than a deserving man: I need more. I don’t eat less hearty than him; and I drink a lot more. I want a bit of amusement, cause I’m a thinking man. I want cheerfulness and a song and a band when I feel low. Well, they charge me just the same for everything as they charge the deserving. What is middle class morality? Just an excuse for never giving me anything. Therefore, I ask you, as two gentlemen, not to play that game on me. I’m playing straight with you. I ain’t pretending to be deserving. I’m undeserving; and I mean to go on being undeserving. I like it; and that’s the truth. Will you take advantage of a man’s nature to do him out of the price of his own daughter what he’s brought up and fed and clothed by the sweat of his brow until she’s growed big enough to be interesting to you two gentlemen? Is five pounds unreasonable? I put it to you; and I leave it to you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising, and going over to Pickering] Pickering: if we were to take this man in hand for three months, he could choose between a seat in the Cabinet and a popular pulpit in Wales.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. What do you say to that, Doolittle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Not me, Governor, thank you kindly. I’ve heard all the preachers and all the prime ministers—for I’m a thinking man and game for politics or religion or social reform same as all the other amusements—and I tell you it’s a dog’s life anyway you look at it. Undeserving poverty is my line. Taking one station in society with another, it’s—it’s—well, it’s the only one that has any ginger in it, to my taste.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I suppose we must give him a fiver.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. He’ll make a bad use of it, I’m afraid.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Not me, Governor, so help me I won’t. Don’t you be afraid that I’ll save it and spare it and live idle on it. There won’t be a penny of it left by Monday: I’ll have to go to work same as if I’d never had it. It won’t pauperize me, you bet. Just one good spree for myself and the missus, giving pleasure to ourselves and employment to others, and satisfaction to you to think it’s not been throwed away. You couldn’t spend it better.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [taking out his pocket book and coming between Doolittle and the piano] This is irresistible. Let’s give him ten. [He offers two notes to the dustman].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. No, Governor. She wouldn’t have the heart to spend ten; and perhaps I shouldn’t neither. Ten pounds is a lot of money: it makes a man feel prudent like; and then goodbye to happiness. You give me what I ask you, Governor: not a penny more, and not a penny less.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Why don’t you marry that missus of yours? I rather draw the line at encouraging that sort of immorality.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Tell her so, Governor: tell her so. I’m willing. It’s me that suffers by it. I’ve no hold on her. I got to be agreeable to her. I got to give her presents. I got to buy her clothes something sinful. I’m a slave to that woman, Governor, just because I’m not her lawful husband. And she knows it too. Catch her marrying me! Take my advice, Governor: marry Eliza while she’s young and don’t know no better. If you don’t you’ll be sorry for it after. If you do, she’ll be sorry for it after; but better you than her, because you’re a man, and she’s only a woman and don’t know how to be happy anyhow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Pickering: if we listen to this man another minute, we shall have no convictions left. [To Doolittle] Five pounds I think you said.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Thank you kindly, Governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You’re sure you won’t take ten?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Not now. Another time, Governor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [handing him a five-pound note] Here you are.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Thank you, Governor. Good morning.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">[He hurries to the door, anxious to get away with his booty. When he opens it he is confronted with a dainty and exquisitely clean young Japanese lady in a simple blue cotton kimono printed cunningly with small white jasmine blossoms. Mrs. Pearce is with her. He gets out of her way deferentially and apologizes]. Beg pardon, miss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE JAPANESE LADY. Garn! Don’t you know your own daughter?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">DOOLITTLE {exclaiming    Bly me! it’s Eliza!<br>\nHIGGINS {simul-               What’s that! This!<br>\nPICKERING {taneously     By Jove!<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Don’t I look silly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Silly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [at the door] Now, Mr. Higgins, please don’t say anything to make the girl conceited about herself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [conscientiously] Oh! Quite right, Mrs. Pearce. [To Eliza] Yes: damned silly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Please, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [correcting himself] I mean extremely silly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I should look all right with my hat on. [She takes up her hat; puts it on; and walks across the room to the fireplace with a fashionable air].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. A new fashion, by George! And it ought to look horrible!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [with fatherly pride] Well, I never thought she’d clean up as good looking as that, Governor. She’s a credit to me, ain’t she?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I tell you, it’s easy to clean up here. Hot and cold water on tap, just as much as you like, there is. Woolly towels, there is; and a towel horse so hot, it burns your fingers. Soft brushes to scrub yourself, and a wooden bowl of soap smelling like primroses. Now I know why ladies is so clean. Washing’s a treat for them. Wish they saw what it is for the like of me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I’m glad the bath-room met with your approval.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. It didn’t: not all of it; and I don’t care who hears me say it. Mrs. Pearce knows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What was wrong, Mrs. Pearce?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [blandly] Oh, nothing, sir. It doesn’t matter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I had a good mind to break it. I didn’t know which way to look. But I hung a towel over it, I did.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Over what?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE. Over the looking-glass, sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Doolittle: you have brought your daughter up too strictly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Me! I never brought her up at all, except to give her a lick of a strap now and again. Don’t put it on me, Governor. She ain’t accustomed to it, you see: that’s all. But she’ll soon pick up your free-and-easy ways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I’m a good girl, I am; and I won’t pick up no free and easy ways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Eliza: if you say again that you’re a good girl, your father shall take you home.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Not him. You don’t know my father. All he come here for was to touch you for some money to get drunk on.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Well, what else would I want money for? To put into the plate in church, I suppose. [She puts out her tongue at him. He is so incensed by this that Pickering presently finds it necessary to step between them]. Don’t you give me none of your lip; and don’t let me hear you giving this gentleman any of it neither, or you’ll hear from me about it. See?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Have you any further advice to give her before you go, Doolittle? Your blessing, for instance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. No, Governor: I ain’t such a mug as to put up my children to all I know myself. Hard enough to hold them in without that. If you want Eliza’s mind improved, Governor, you do it yourself with a strap. So long, gentlemen. [He turns to go].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [impressively] Stop. You’ll come regularly to see your daughter. It’s your duty, you know. My brother is a clergyman; and he could help you in your talks with her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [evasively] Certainly. I’ll come, Governor. Not just this week, because I have a job at a distance. But later on you may depend on me. Afternoon, gentlemen. Afternoon, ma’am. [He takes off his hat to Mrs. Pearce, who disdains the salutation and goes out. He winks at Higgins, thinking him probably a fellow sufferer from Mrs. Pearce’s difficult disposition, and follows her].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Don’t you believe the old liar. He’d as soon you set a bull-dog on him as a clergyman. You won’t see him again in a hurry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I don’t want to, Eliza. Do you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Not me. I don’t want never to see him again, I don’t. He’s a disgrace to me, he is, collecting dust, instead of working at his trade.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. What is his trade, Eliza?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Talking money out of other people’s pockets into his own. His proper trade’s a navvy; and he works at it sometimes too—for exercise—and earns good money at it. Ain’t you going to call me Miss Doolittle any more?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I beg your pardon, Miss Doolittle. It was a slip of the tongue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, I don’t mind; only it sounded so genteel. I should just like to take a taxi to the corner of Tottenham Court Road and get out there and tell it to wait for me, just to put the girls in their place a bit. I wouldn’t speak to them, you know.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Better wait til we get you something really fashionable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Besides, you shouldn’t cut your old friends now that you have risen in the world. That’s what we call snobbery.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You don’t call the like of them my friends now, I should hope. They’ve took it out of me often enough with their ridicule when they had the chance; and now I mean to get a bit of my own back. But if I’m to have fashionable clothes, I’ll wait. I should like to have some. Mrs. Pearce says you’re going to give me some to wear in bed at night different to what I wear in the daytime; but it do seem a waste of money when you could get something to show. Besides, I never could fancy changing into cold things on a winter night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [coming back] Now, Eliza. The new things have come for you to try on.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Ah—ow—oo—ooh! [She rushes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. PEARCE [following her] Oh, don’t rush about like that, girl [She shuts the door behind her].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Pickering: we have taken on a stiff job.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [with conviction] Higgins: we have.<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>ACT III</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">It is Mrs. Higgins’s at-home day. Nobody has yet arrived. Her drawing-room, in a flat on Chelsea embankment, has three windows looking on the river; and the ceiling is not so lofty as it would be in an older house of the same pretension. The windows are open, giving access to a balcony with flowers in pots. If you stand with your face to the windows, you have the fireplace on your left and the door in the right-hand wall close to the corner nearest the windows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Mrs. Higgins was brought up on Morris and Burne Jones; and her room, which is very unlike her son’s room in Wimpole Street, is not crowded with furniture and little tables and nicknacks. In the middle of the room there is a big ottoman; and this, with the carpet, the Morris wall-papers, and the Morris chintz window curtains and brocade covers of the ottoman and its cushions, supply all the ornament, and are much too handsome to be hidden by odds and ends of useless things. A few good oil-paintings from the exhibitions in the Grosvenor Gallery thirty years ago (the Burne Jones, not the Whistler side of them) are on the walls. The only landscape is a Cecil Lawson on the scale of a Rubens. There is a portrait of Mrs. Higgins as she was when she defied fashion in her youth in one of the beautiful Rossettian costumes which, when caricatured by people who did not understand, led to the absurdities of popular estheticism in the eighteen-seventies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">In the corner diagonally opposite the door Mrs. Higgins, now over sixty and long past taking the trouble to dress out of the fashion, sits writing at an elegantly simple writing-table with a bell button within reach of her hand. There is a Chippendale chair further back in the room between her and the window nearest her side. At the other side of the room, further forward, is an Elizabethan chair roughly carved in the taste of Inigo Jones. On the same side a piano in a decorated case. The corner between the fireplace and the window is occupied by a divan cushioned in Morris chintz.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">It is between four and five in the afternoon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">The door is opened violently; and Higgins enters with his hat on.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [dismayed] Henry [scolding him]! What are you doing here to-day? It is my at home day: you promised not to come. [As he bends to kiss her, she takes his hat off, and presents it to him].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh bother! [He throws the hat down on the table].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Go home at once.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [kissing her] I know, mother. I came on purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. But you mustn’t. I’m serious, Henry. You offend all my friends: they stop coming whenever they meet you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Nonsense! I know I have no small talk; but people don’t mind. [He sits on the settee].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Oh! don’t they? Small talk indeed! What about your large talk? Really, dear, you mustn’t stay.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I must. I’ve a job for you. A phonetic job.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. No use, dear. I’m sorry; but I can’t get round your vowels; and though I like to get pretty postcards in your patent shorthand, I always have to read the copies in ordinary writing you so thoughtfully send me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, this isn’t a phonetic job.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. You said it was.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Not your part of it. I’ve picked up a girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Does that mean that some girl has picked you up?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Not at all. I don’t mean a love affair.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. What a pity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Why?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Well, you never fall in love with anyone under forty-five. When will you discover that there are some rather nice-looking young women about?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, I can’t be bothered with young women. My idea of a loveable woman is something as like you as possible. I shall never get into the way of seriously liking young women: some habits lie too deep to be changed. [Rising abruptly and walking about, jingling his money and his keys in his trouser pockets] Besides, they’re all idiots.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Do you know what you would do if you really loved me, Henry?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh bother! What? Marry, I suppose?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. No. Stop fidgeting and take your hands out of your pockets. [With a gesture of despair, he obeys and sits down again]. That’s a good boy. Now tell me about the girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. She’s coming to see you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. I don’t remember asking her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You didn’t. I asked her. If you’d known her you wouldn’t have asked her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Indeed! Why?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, it’s like this. She’s a common flower girl. I picked her off the kerbstone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. And invited her to my at-home!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising and coming to her to coax her] Oh, that’ll be all right. I’ve taught her to speak properly; and she has strict orders as to her behavior. She’s to keep to two subjects: the weather and everybody’s health—Fine day and How do you do, you know—and not to let herself go on things in general. That will be safe.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Safe! To talk about our health! about our insides! perhaps about our outsides! How could you be so silly, Henry?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [impatiently] Well, she must talk about something. [He controls himself and sits down again]. Oh, she’ll be all right: don’t you fuss. Pickering is in it with me. I’ve a sort of bet on that I’ll pass her off as a duchess in six months. I started on her some months ago; and she’s getting on like a house on fire. I shall win my bet. She has a quick ear; and she’s been easier to teach than my middle-class pupils because she’s had to learn a complete new language. She talks English almost as you talk French.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. That’s satisfactory, at all events.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, it is and it isn’t.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. What does that mean?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You see, I’ve got her pronunciation all right; but you have to consider not only how a girl pronounces, but what she pronounces; and that’s where—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">They are interrupted by the parlor-maid, announcing guests.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Mrs. and Miss Eynsford Hill. [She withdraws].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh Lord! [He rises; snatches his hat from the table; and makes for the door; but before he reaches it his mother introduces him].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. and Miss Eynsford Hill are the mother and daughter who sheltered from the rain in Covent Garden. The mother is well bred, quiet, and has the habitual anxiety of straitened means. The daughter has acquired a gay air of being very much at home in society: the bravado of genteel poverty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [to Mrs. Higgins] How do you do? [They shake hands].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MISS EYNSFORD HILL. How d’you do? [She shakes].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [introducing] My son Henry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. Your celebrated son! I have so longed to meet you, Professor Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [glumly, making no movement in her direction] Delighted. [He backs against the piano and bows brusquely].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">Miss EYNSFORD HILL [going to him with confident familiarity] How do you do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [staring at her] I’ve seen you before somewhere. I haven’t the ghost of a notion where; but I’ve heard your voice. [Drearily] It doesn’t matter. You’d better sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. I’m sorry to say that my celebrated son has no manners. You mustn’t mind him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MISS EYNSFORD HILL [gaily] I don’t. [She sits in the Elizabethan chair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [a little bewildered] Not at all. [She sits on the ottoman between her daughter and Mrs. Higgins, who has turned her chair away from the writing-table].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, have I been rude? I didn’t mean to be. [He goes to the central window, through which, with his back to the company, he contemplates the river and the flowers in Battersea Park on the opposite bank as if they were a frozen dessert.]</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The parlor-maid returns, ushering in Pickering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Colonel Pickering [She withdraws].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. How do you do, Mrs. Higgins?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. So glad you’ve come. Do you know Mrs. Eynsford Hill—Miss Eynsford Hill? [Exchange of bows. The Colonel brings the Chippendale chair a little forward between Mrs. Hill and Mrs. Higgins, and sits down].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Has Henry told you what we’ve come for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [over his shoulder] We were interrupted: damn it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Oh Henry, Henry, really!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [half rising] Are we in the way?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [rising and making her sit down again] No, no. You couldn’t have come more fortunately: we want you to meet a friend of ours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [turning hopefully] Yes, by George! We want two or three people. You’ll do as well as anybody else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The parlor-maid returns, ushering Freddy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Mr. Eynsford Hill.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [almost audibly, past endurance] God of Heaven! another of them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [shaking hands with Mrs. Higgins] Ahdedo?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Very good of you to come. [Introducing] Colonel Pickering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [bowing] Ahdedo?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. I don’t think you know my son, Professor Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [going to Higgins] Ahdedo?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [looking at him much as if he were a pickpocket] I’ll take my oath I’ve met you before somewhere. Where was it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. I don’t think so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [resignedly] It don’t matter, anyhow. Sit down. He shakes Freddy’s hand, and almost slings him on the ottoman with his face to the windows; then comes round to the other side of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, here we are, anyhow! [He sits down on the ottoman next Mrs. Eynsford Hill, on her left.] And now, what the devil are we going to talk about until Eliza comes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Henry: you are the life and soul of the Royal Society’s soirees; but really you’re rather trying on more commonplace occasions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Am I? Very sorry. [Beaming suddenly] I suppose I am, you know. [Uproariously] Ha, ha!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MISS EYNSFORD HILL [who considers Higgins quite eligible matrimonially] I sympathize. I haven’t any small talk. If people would only be frank and say what they really think!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [relapsing into gloom] Lord forbid!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [taking up her daughter’s cue] But why?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What they think they ought to think is bad enough, Lord knows; but what they really think would break up the whole show. Do you suppose it would be really agreeable if I were to come out now with what I really think?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MISS EYNSFORD HILL [gaily] Is it so very cynical?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Cynical! Who the dickens said it was cynical? I mean it wouldn’t be decent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [seriously] Oh! I’m sure you don’t mean that, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You see, we’re all savages, more or less. We’re supposed to be civilized and cultured—to know all about poetry and philosophy and art and science, and so on; but how many of us know even the meanings of these names? [To Miss Hill] What do you know of poetry? [To Mrs. Hill] What do you know of science? [Indicating Freddy] What does he know of art or science or anything else? What the devil do you imagine I know of philosophy?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [warningly] Or of manners, Henry?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID [opening the door] Miss Doolittle. [She withdraws].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising hastily and running to Mrs. Higgins] Here she is, mother. [He stands on tiptoe and makes signs over his mother’s head to Eliza to indicate to her which lady is her hostess].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza, who is exquisitely dressed, produces an impression of such remarkable distinction and beauty as she enters that they all rise, quite flustered. Guided by Higgins’s signals, she comes to Mrs. Higgins with studied grace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [speaking with pedantic correctness of pronunciation and great beauty of tone] How do you do, Mrs. Higgins? [She gasps slightly in making sure of the H in Higgins, but is quite successful]. Mr. Higgins told me I might come.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [cordially] Quite right: I’m very glad indeed to see you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. How do you do, Miss Doolittle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [shaking hands with him] Colonel Pickering, is it not?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. I feel sure we have met before, Miss Doolittle. I remember your eyes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. How do you do? [She sits down on the ottoman gracefully in the place just left vacant by Higgins].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [introducing] My daughter Clara.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. How do you do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA [impulsively] How do you do? [She sits down on the ottoman beside Eliza, devouring her with her eyes].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [coming to their side of the ottoman] I’ve certainly had the pleasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [introducing] My son Freddy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. How do you do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Freddy bows and sits down in the Elizabethan chair, infatuated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [suddenly] By George, yes: it all comes back to me! [They stare at him]. Covent Garden! [Lamentably] What a damned thing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Henry, please! [He is about to sit on the edge of the table]. Don’t sit on my writing-table: you’ll break it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [sulkily] Sorry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">He goes to the divan, stumbling into the fender and over the fire-irons on his way; extricating himself with muttered imprecations; and finishing his disastrous journey by throwing himself so impatiently on the divan that he almost breaks it. Mrs. Higgins looks at him, but controls herself and says nothing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">A long and painful pause ensues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [at last, conversationally] Will it rain, do you think?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. The shallow depression in the west of these islands is likely to move slowly in an easterly direction. There are no indications of any great change in the barometrical situation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Ha! ha! how awfully funny!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What is wrong with that, young man? I bet I got it right.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Killing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. I’m sure I hope it won’t turn cold. There’s so much influenza about. It runs right through our whole family regularly every spring.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [darkly] My aunt died of influenza: so they said.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [clicks her tongue sympathetically]!!!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [in the same tragic tone] But it’s my belief they done the old woman in.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [puzzled] Done her in?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Y-e-e-e-es, Lord love you! Why should she die of influenza? She come through diphtheria right enough the year before. I saw her with my own eyes. Fairly blue with it, she was. They all thought she was dead; but my father he kept ladling gin down her throat til she came to so sudden that she bit the bowl off the spoon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [startled] Dear me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [piling up the indictment] What call would a woman with that strength in her have to die of influenza? What become of her new straw hat that should have come to me? Somebody pinched it; and what I say is, them as pinched it done her in.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. What does doing her in mean?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [hastily] Oh, that’s the new small talk. To do a person in means to kill them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [to Eliza, horrified] You surely don’t believe that your aunt was killed?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Do I not! Them she lived with would have killed her for a hat-pin, let alone a hat.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. But it can’t have been right for your father to pour spirits down her throat like that. It might have killed her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Not her. Gin was mother’s milk to her. Besides, he’d poured so much down his own throat that he knew the good of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. Do you mean that he drank?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Drank! My word! Something chronic.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. How dreadful for you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Not a bit. It never did him no harm what I could see. But then he did not keep it up regular. [Cheerfully] On the burst, as you might say, from time to time. And always more agreeable when he had a drop in. When he was out of work, my mother used to give him fourpence and tell him to go out and not come back until he’d drunk himself cheerful and loving-like. There’s lots of women has to make their husbands drunk to make them fit to live with. [Now quite at her ease] You see, it’s like this. If a man has a bit of a conscience, it always takes him when he’s sober; and then it makes him low-spirited. A drop of booze just takes that off and makes him happy. [To Freddy, who is in convulsions of suppressed laughter] Here! what are you sniggering at?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. The new small talk. You do it so awfully well.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. If I was doing it proper, what was you laughing at? [To Higgins] Have I said anything I oughtn’t?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [interposing] Not at all, Miss Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Well, that’s a mercy, anyhow. [Expansively] What I always say is—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising and looking at his watch] Ahem!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [looking round at him; taking the hint; and rising] Well: I must go. [They all rise. Freddy goes to the door]. So pleased to have met you. Good-bye. [She shakes hands with Mrs. Higgins].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Good-bye, Colonel Pickering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Good-bye, Miss Doolittle. [They shake hands].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [nodding to the others] Good-bye, all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [opening the door for her] Are you walking across the Park, Miss Doolittle? If so—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Walk! Not bloody likely. [Sensation]. I am going in a taxi. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">Pickering gasps and sits down. Freddy goes out on the balcony to catch another glimpse of Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [suffering from shock] Well, I really can’t get used to the new ways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA [throwing herself discontentedly into the Elizabethan chair]. Oh, it’s all right, mamma, quite right. People will think we never go anywhere or see anybody if you are so old-fashioned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. I daresay I am very old-fashioned; but I do hope you won’t begin using that expression, Clara. I have got accustomed to hear you talking about men as rotters, and calling everything filthy and beastly; though I do think it horrible and unladylike. But this last is really too much. Don’t you think so, Colonel Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Don’t ask me. I’ve been away in India for several years; and manners have changed so much that I sometimes don’t know whether I’m at a respectable dinner-table or in a ship’s forecastle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA. It’s all a matter of habit. There’s no right or wrong in it. Nobody means anything by it. And it’s so quaint, and gives such a smart emphasis to things that are not in themselves very witty. I find the new small talk delightful and quite innocent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [rising] Well, after that, I think it’s time for us to go.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Pickering and Higgins rise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA [rising] Oh yes: we have three at homes to go to still. Good-bye, Mrs. Higgins. Good-bye, Colonel Pickering. Good-bye, Professor Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [coming grimly at her from the divan, and accompanying her to the door] Good-bye. Be sure you try on that small talk at the three at-homes. Don’t be nervous about it. Pitch it in strong.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA [all smiles] I will. Good-bye. Such nonsense, all this early Victorian prudery!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [tempting her] Such damned nonsense!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA. Such bloody nonsense!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [convulsively] Clara!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">CLARA. Ha! ha! [She goes out radiant, conscious of being thoroughly up to date, and is heard descending the stairs in a stream of silvery laughter].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [to the heavens at large] Well, I ask you [He gives it up, and comes to Mrs. Higgins]. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [shaking hands] Good-bye. Would you like to meet Miss Doolittle again?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY [eagerly] Yes, I should, most awfully.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Well, you know my days.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">FREDDY. Yes. Thanks awfully. Good-bye. [He goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. Good-bye, Mr. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Good-bye. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [to Pickering] It’s no use. I shall never be able to bring myself to use that word.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Don’t. It’s not compulsory, you know. You’ll get on quite well without it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. Only, Clara is so down on me if I am not positively reeking with the latest slang. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Good-bye [They shake hands].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL [to Mrs. Higgins] You mustn’t mind Clara. [Pickering, catching from her lowered tone that this is not meant for him to hear, discreetly joins Higgins at the window]. We’re so poor! and she gets so few parties, poor child! She doesn’t quite know. [Mrs. Higgins, seeing that her eyes are moist, takes her hand sympathetically and goes with her to the door]. But the boy is nice. Don’t you think so?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Oh, quite nice. I shall always be delighted to see him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. EYNSFORD HILL. Thank you, dear. Good-bye. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [eagerly] Well? Is Eliza presentable [he swoops on his mother and drags her to the ottoman, where she sits down in Eliza’s place with her son on her left]?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Pickering returns to his chair on her right.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. You silly boy, of course she’s not presentable. She’s a triumph of your art and of her dressmaker’s; but if you suppose for a moment that she doesn’t give herself away in every sentence she utters, you must be perfectly cracked about her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. But don’t you think something might be done? I mean something to eliminate the sanguinary element from her conversation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Not as long as she is in Henry’s hands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [aggrieved] Do you mean that my language is improper?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. No, dearest: it would be quite proper—say on a canal barge; but it would not be proper for her at a garden party.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [deeply injured] Well I must say—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [interrupting him] Come, Higgins: you must learn to know yourself. I haven’t heard such language as yours since we used to review the volunteers in Hyde Park twenty years ago.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [sulkily] Oh, well, if you say so, I suppose I don’t always talk like a bishop.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [quieting Henry with a touch] Colonel Pickering: will you tell me what is the exact state of things in Wimpole Street?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [cheerfully: as if this completely changed the subject] Well, I have come to live there with Henry. We work together at my Indian Dialects; and we think it more convenient—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Quite so. I know all about that: it’s an excellent arrangement. But where does this girl live?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. With us, of course. Where would she live?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. But on what terms? Is she a servant? If not, what is she?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [slowly] I think I know what you mean, Mrs. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, dash me if I do! I’ve had to work at the girl every day for months to get her to her present pitch. Besides, she’s useful. She knows where my things are, and remembers my appointments and so forth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. How does your housekeeper get on with her?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Mrs. Pearce? Oh, she’s jolly glad to get so much taken off her hands; for before Eliza came, she had to have to find things and remind me of my appointments. But she’s got some silly bee in her bonnet about Eliza. She keeps saying “You don’t think, sir”: doesn’t she, Pick?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Yes: that’s the formula. “You don’t think, sir.” That’s the end of every conversation about Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. As if I ever stop thinking about the girl and her confounded vowels and consonants. I’m worn out, thinking about her, and watching her lips and her teeth and her tongue, not to mention her soul, which is the quaintest of the lot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. You certainly are a pretty pair of babies, playing with your live doll.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Playing! The hardest job I ever tackled: make no mistake about that, mother. But you have no idea how frightfully interesting it is to take a human being and change her into a quite different human being by creating a new speech for her. It’s filling up the deepest gulf that separates class from class and soul from soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [drawing his chair closer to Mrs. Higgins and bending over to her eagerly] Yes: it’s enormously interesting. I assure you, Mrs. Higgins, we take Eliza very seriously. Every week—every day almost—there is some new change. [Closer again] We keep records of every stage—dozens of gramophone disks and photographs—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [assailing her at the other ear] Yes, by George: it’s the most absorbing experiment I ever tackled. She regularly fills our lives up; doesn’t she, Pick?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. We’re always talking Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Teaching Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Dressing Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. What!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Inventing new Elizas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins and Pickering, speaking together:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">HIGGINS.       You know, she has the most extraordinary quickness of ear:<br>\nPICKERING.   I assure you, my dear Mrs. Higgins, that girl<br>\nHIGGINS.       just like a parrot. I’ve tried her with every<br>\nPICKERING.   is a genius. She can play the piano quite beautifully<br>\nHIGGINS.       possible sort of sound that a human being can make—<br>\nPICKERING.   We have taken her to classical concerts and to music<br>\nHIGGINS.       Continental dialects, African dialects, Hottentot<br>\nPICKERING.   halls; and it’s all the same to her: she plays everything<br>\nHIGGINS.       clicks, things it took me years to get hold of; and<br>\nPICKERING.   she hears right off when she comes home, whether it’s<br>\nHIGGINS.       she picks them up like a shot, right away, as if she had<br>\nPICKERING.   Beethoven and Brahms or Lehar and Lionel Morickton;<br>\nHIGGINS.       been at it all her life.<br>\nPICKERING.   though six months ago, she’d never as much as touched a piano.<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [putting her fingers in her ears, as they are by this time shouting one another down with an intolerable noise] Sh—sh—sh—sh! [They stop].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I beg your pardon. [He draws his chair back apologetically].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Sorry. When Pickering starts shouting nobody can get a word in edgeways.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Be quiet, Henry. Colonel Pickering: don’t you realize that when Eliza walked into Wimpole Street, something walked in with her?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Her father did. But Henry soon got rid of him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. It would have been more to the point if her mother had. But as her mother didn’t something else did.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. But what?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [unconsciously dating herself by the word] A problem.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh, I see. The problem of how to pass her off as a lady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I’ll solve that problem. I’ve half solved it already.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. No, you two infinitely stupid male creatures: the problem of what is to be done with her afterwards.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I don’t see anything in that. She can go her own way, with all the advantages I have given her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. The advantages of that poor woman who was here just now! The manners and habits that disqualify a fine lady from earning her own living without giving her a fine lady’s income! Is that what you mean?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [indulgently, being rather bored] Oh, that will be all right, Mrs. Higgins. [He rises to go].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising also] We’ll find her some light employment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. She’s happy enough. Don’t you worry about her. Good-bye. [He shakes hands as if he were consoling a frightened child, and makes for the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Anyhow, there’s no good bothering now. The thing’s done. Good-bye, mother. [He kisses her, and follows Pickering].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [turning for a final consolation] There are plenty of openings. We’ll do what’s right. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [to Pickering as they go out together] Let’s take her to the Shakespear exhibition at Earls Court.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Yes: let’s. Her remarks will be delicious.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. She’ll mimic all the people for us when we get home.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Ripping. [Both are heard laughing as they go downstairs].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [rises with an impatient bounce, and returns to her work at the writing-table. She sweeps a litter of disarranged papers out of her way; snatches a sheet of paper from her stationery case; and tries resolutely to write. At the third line she gives it up; flings down her pen; grips the table angrily and exclaims] Oh, men! men!! men!!!<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>ACT IV</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">The Wimpole Street laboratory. Midnight. Nobody in the room. The clock on the mantelpiece strikes twelve. The fire is not alight: it is a summer night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Presently Higgins and Pickering are heard on the stairs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [calling down to Pickering] I say, Pick: lock up, will you. I shan’t be going out again.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Right. Can Mrs. Pearce go to bed? We don’t want anything more, do we?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Lord, no!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza opens the door and is seen on the lighted landing in opera cloak, brilliant evening dress, and diamonds, with fan, flowers, and all accessories. She comes to the hearth, and switches on the electric lights there. She is tired: her pallor contrasts strongly with her dark eyes and hair; and her expression is almost tragic. She takes off her cloak; puts her fan and flowers on the piano; and sits down on the bench, brooding and silent. Higgins, in evening dress, with overcoat and hat, comes in, carrying a smoking jacket which he has picked up downstairs. He takes off the hat and overcoat; throws them carelessly on the newspaper stand; disposes of his coat in the same way; puts on the smoking jacket; and throws himself wearily into the easy-chair at the hearth. Pickering, similarly attired, comes in. He also takes off his hat and overcoat, and is about to throw them on Higgins’s when he hesitates.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I say: Mrs. Pearce will row if we leave these things lying about in the drawing-room.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, chuck them over the bannisters into the hall. She’ll find them there in the morning and put them away all right. She’ll think we were drunk.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. We are, slightly. Are there any letters?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I didn’t look. [Pickering takes the overcoats and hats and goes down stairs. Higgins begins half singing half yawning an air from La Fanciulla del Golden West. Suddenly he stops and exclaims] I wonder where the devil my slippers are!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza looks at him darkly; then leaves the room.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins yawns again, and resumes his song. Pickering returns, with the contents of the letter-box in his hand.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Only circulars, and this coroneted billet-doux for you. [He throws the circulars into the fender, and posts himself on the hearthrug, with his back to the grate].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [glancing at the billet-doux] Money-lender. [He throws the letter after the circulars].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza returns with a pair of large down-at-heel slippers. She places them on the carpet before Higgins, and sits as before without a word.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [yawning again] Oh Lord! What an evening! What a crew! What a silly tomfoollery! [He raises his shoe to unlace it, and catches sight of the slippers. He stops unlacing and looks at them as if they had appeared there of their own accord]. Oh! they’re there, are they?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [stretching himself] Well, I feel a bit tired. It’s been a long day. The garden party, a dinner party, and the opera! Rather too much of a good thing. But you’ve won your bet, Higgins. Eliza did the trick, and something to spare, eh?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [fervently] Thank God it’s over!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza flinches violently; but they take no notice of her; and she recovers herself and sits stonily as before.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Were you nervous at the garden party? I was. Eliza didn’t seem a bit nervous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, she wasn’t nervous. I knew she’d be all right. No, it’s the strain of putting the job through all these months that has told on me. It was interesting enough at first, while we were at the phonetics; but after that I got deadly sick of it. If I hadn’t backed myself to do it I should have chucked the whole thing up two months ago. It was a silly notion: the whole thing has been a bore.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh come! the garden party was frightfully exciting. My heart began beating like anything.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes, for the first three minutes. But when I saw we were going to win hands down, I felt like a bear in a cage, hanging about doing nothing. The dinner was worse: sitting gorging there for over an hour, with nobody but a damned fool of a fashionable woman to talk to! I tell you, Pickering, never again for me. No more artificial duchesses. The whole thing has been simple purgatory.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. You’ve never been broken in properly to the social routine. [Strolling over to the piano] I rather enjoy dipping into it occasionally myself: it makes me feel young again. Anyhow, it was a great success: an immense success. I was quite frightened once or twice because Eliza was doing it so well. You see, lots of the real people can’t do it at all: they’re such fools that they think style comes by nature to people in their position; and so they never learn. There’s always something professional about doing a thing superlatively well.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes: that’s what drives me mad: the silly people don’t know their own silly business. [Rising] However, it’s over and done with; and now I can go to bed at last without dreading tomorrow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza’s beauty becomes murderous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I think I shall turn in too. Still, it’s been a great occasion: a triumph for you. Good-night. [He goes].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [following him] Good-night. [Over his shoulder, at the door] Put out the lights, Eliza; and tell Mrs. Pearce not to make coffee for me in the morning: I’ll take tea. [He goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza tries to control herself and feel indifferent as she rises and walks across to the hearth to switch off the lights. By the time she gets there she is on the point of screaming. She sits down in Higgins’s chair and holds on hard to the arms. Finally she gives way and flings herself furiously on the floor raging.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [in despairing wrath outside] What the devil have I done with my slippers? [He appears at the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [snatching up the slippers, and hurling them at him one after the other with all her force] There are your slippers. And there. Take your slippers; and may you never have a day’s luck with them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [astounded] What on earth—! [He comes to her]. What’s the matter? Get up. [He pulls her up]. Anything wrong?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [breathless] Nothing wrong—with YOU. I’ve won your bet for you, haven’t I? That’s enough for you. <i>I</i> don’t matter, I suppose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. YOU won my bet! You! Presumptuous insect! <i>I</i> won it. What did you throw those slippers at me for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Because I wanted to smash your face. I’d like to kill you, you selfish brute. Why didn’t you leave me where you picked me out of—in the gutter? You thank God it’s all over, and that now you can throw me back again there, do you? [She crisps her fingers, frantically].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [looking at her in cool wonder] The creature IS nervous, after all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [gives a suffocated scream of fury, and instinctively darts her nails at his face]!!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [catching her wrists] Ah! would you? Claws in, you cat. How dare you show your temper to me? Sit down and be quiet. [He throws her roughly into the easy-chair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [crushed by superior strength and weight] What’s to become of me? What’s to become of me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. How the devil do I know what’s to become of you? What does it matter what becomes of you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You don’t care. I know you don’t care. You wouldn’t care if I was dead. I’m nothing to you—not so much as them slippers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [thundering] THOSE slippers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [with bitter submission] Those slippers. I didn’t think it made any difference now.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">A pause. Eliza hopeless and crushed. Higgins a little uneasy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [in his loftiest manner] Why have you begun going on like this? May I ask whether you complain of your treatment here?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Has anybody behaved badly to you? Colonel Pickering? Mrs. Pearce? Any of the servants?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I presume you don’t pretend that I have treated you badly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I am glad to hear it. [He moderates his tone]. Perhaps you’re tired after the strain of the day. Will you have a glass of champagne? [He moves towards the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No. [Recollecting her manners] Thank you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [good-humored again] This has been coming on you for some days. I suppose it was natural for you to be anxious about the garden party. But that’s all over now. [He pats her kindly on the shoulder. She writhes]. There’s nothing more to worry about.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No. Nothing more for you to worry about. [She suddenly rises and gets away from him by going to the piano bench, where she sits and hides her face]. Oh God! I wish I was dead.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [staring after her in sincere surprise] Why? in heaven’s name, why? [Reasonably, going to her] Listen to me, Eliza. All this irritation is purely subjective.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I don’t understand. I’m too ignorant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. It’s only imagination. Low spirits and nothing else. Nobody’s hurting you. Nothing’s wrong. You go to bed like a good girl and sleep it off. Have a little cry and say your prayers: that will make you comfortable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I heard YOUR prayers. “Thank God it’s all over!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [impatiently] Well, don’t you thank God it’s all over? Now you are free and can do what you like.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [pulling herself together in desperation] What am I fit for? What have you left me fit for? Where am I to go? What am I to do? What’s to become of me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [enlightened, but not at all impressed] Oh, that’s what’s worrying you, is it? [He thrusts his hands into his pockets, and walks about in his usual manner, rattling the contents of his pockets, as if condescending to a trivial subject out of pure kindness]. I shouldn’t bother about it if I were you. I should imagine you won’t have much difficulty in settling yourself, somewhere or other, though I hadn’t quite realized that you were going away. [She looks quickly at him: he does not look at her, but examines the dessert stand on the piano and decides that he will eat an apple]. You might marry, you know. [He bites a large piece out of the apple, and munches it noisily]. You see, Eliza, all men are not confirmed old bachelors like me and the Colonel. Most men are the marrying sort (poor devils!); and you’re not bad-looking; it’s quite a pleasure to look at you sometimes—not now, of course, because you’re crying and looking as ugly as the very devil; but when you’re all right and quite yourself, you’re what I should call attractive. That is, to the people in the marrying line, you understand. You go to bed and have a good nice rest; and then get up and look at yourself in the glass; and you won’t feel so cheap.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza again looks at him, speechless, and does not stir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The look is quite lost on him: he eats his apple with a dreamy expression of happiness, as it is quite a good one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [a genial afterthought occurring to him] I daresay my mother could find some chap or other who would do very well—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. We were above that at the corner of Tottenham Court Road.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [waking up] What do you mean?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I sold flowers. I didn’t sell myself. Now you’ve made a lady of me I’m not fit to sell anything else. I wish you’d left me where you found me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [slinging the core of the apple decisively into the grate] Tosh, Eliza. Don’t you insult human relations by dragging all this cant about buying and selling into it. You needn’t marry the fellow if you don’t like him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What else am I to do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, lots of things. What about your old idea of a florist’s shop? Pickering could set you up in one: he’s lots of money. [Chuckling] He’ll have to pay for all those togs you have been wearing today; and that, with the hire of the jewellery, will make a big hole in two hundred pounds. Why, six months ago you would have thought it the millennium to have a flower shop of your own. Come! you’ll be all right. I must clear off to bed: I’m devilish sleepy. By the way, I came down for something: I forget what it was.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Your slippers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh yes, of course. You shied them at me. [He picks them up, and is going out when she rises and speaks to him].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Before you go, sir—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [dropping the slippers in his surprise at her calling him sir] Eh?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Do my clothes belong to me or to Colonel Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [coming back into the room as if her question were the very climax of unreason] What the devil use would they be to Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. He might want them for the next girl you pick up to experiment on.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [shocked and hurt] Is THAT the way you feel towards us?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I don’t want to hear anything more about that. All I want to know is whether anything belongs to me. My own clothes were burnt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. But what does it matter? Why need you start bothering about that in the middle of the night?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I want to know what I may take away with me. I don’t want to be accused of stealing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [now deeply wounded] Stealing! You shouldn’t have said that, Eliza. That shows a want of feeling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I’m sorry. I’m only a common ignorant girl; and in my station I have to be careful. There can’t be any feelings between the like of you and the like of me. Please will you tell me what belongs to me and what doesn’t?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [very sulky] You may take the whole damned houseful if you like. Except the jewels. They’re hired. Will that satisfy you? [He turns on his heel and is about to go in extreme dudgeon].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [drinking in his emotion like nectar, and nagging him to provoke a further supply] Stop, please. [She takes off her jewels]. Will you take these to your room and keep them safe? I don’t want to run the risk of their being missing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [furious] Hand them over. [She puts them into his hands]. If these belonged to me instead of to the jeweler, I’d ram them down your ungrateful throat. [He perfunctorily thrusts them into his pockets, unconsciously decorating himself with the protruding ends of the chains].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [taking a ring off] This ring isn’t the jeweler’s: it’s the one you bought me in Brighton. I don’t want it now. [Higgins dashes the ring violently into the fireplace, and turns on her so threateningly that she crouches over the piano with her hands over her face, and exclaims] Don’t you hit me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Hit you! You infamous creature, how dare you accuse me of such a thing? It is you who have hit me. You have wounded me to the heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [thrilling with hidden joy] I’m glad. I’ve got a little of my own back, anyhow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [with dignity, in his finest professional style] You have caused me to lose my temper: a thing that has hardly ever happened to me before. I prefer to say nothing more tonight. I am going to bed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [pertly] You’d better leave a note for Mrs. Pearce about the coffee; for she won’t be told by me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [formally] Damn Mrs. Pearce; and damn the coffee; and damn you; and damn my own folly in having lavished MY hard-earned knowledge and the treasure of my regard and intimacy on a heartless guttersnipe. [He goes out with impressive decorum, and spoils it by slamming the door savagely].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza smiles for the first time; expresses her feelings by a wild pantomime in which an imitation of Higgins’s exit is confused with her own triumph; and finally goes down on her knees on the hearthrug to look for the ring.<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><h2>ACT V</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"noindent\">Mrs. Higgins’s drawing-room. She is at her writing-table as before. The parlor-maid comes in.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID [at the door] Mr. Henry, mam, is downstairs with Colonel Pickering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Well, show them up.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. They’re using the telephone, mam. Telephoning to the police, I think.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. What!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID [coming further in and lowering her voice] Mr. Henry’s in a state, mam. I thought I’d better tell you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. If you had told me that Mr. Henry was not in a state it would have been more surprising. Tell them to come up when they’ve finished with the police. I suppose he’s lost something.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Yes, maam [going].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Go upstairs and tell Miss Doolittle that Mr. Henry and the Colonel are here. Ask her not to come down till I send for her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Yes, mam.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins bursts in. He is, as the parlor-maid has said, in a state.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Look here, mother: here’s a confounded thing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Yes, dear. Good-morning. [He checks his impatience and kisses her, whilst the parlor-maid goes out]. What is it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Eliza’s bolted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [calmly continuing her writing] You must have frightened her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Frightened her! nonsense! She was left last night, as usual, to turn out the lights and all that; and instead of going to bed she changed her clothes and went right off: her bed wasn’t slept in. She came in a cab for her things before seven this morning; and that fool Mrs. Pearce let her have them without telling me a word about it. What am I to do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Do without, I’m afraid, Henry. The girl has a perfect right to leave if she chooses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [wandering distractedly across the room] But I can’t find anything. I don’t know what appointments I’ve got. I’m— [Pickering comes in. Mrs. Higgins puts down her pen and turns away from the writing-table].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [shaking hands] Good-morning, Mrs. Higgins. Has Henry told you? [He sits down on the ottoman].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What does that ass of an inspector say? Have you offered a reward?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [rising in indignant amazement] You don’t mean to say you have set the police after Eliza?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Of course. What are the police for? What else could we do? [He sits in the Elizabethan chair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. The inspector made a lot of difficulties. I really think he suspected us of some improper purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Well, of course he did. What right have you to go to the police and give the girl’s name as if she were a thief, or a lost umbrella, or something? Really! [She sits down again, deeply vexed].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. But we want to find her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. We can’t let her go like this, you know, Mrs. Higgins. What were we to do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. You have no more sense, either of you, than two children. Why—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The parlor-maid comes in and breaks off the conversation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Mr. Henry: a gentleman wants to see you very particular. He’s been sent on from Wimpole Street.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, bother! I can’t see anyone now. Who is it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. A Mr. Doolittle, Sir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Doolittle! Do you mean the dustman?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Dustman! Oh no, sir: a gentleman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [springing up excitedly] By George, Pick, it’s some relative of hers that she’s gone to. Somebody we know nothing about. [To the parlor-maid] Send him up, quick.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Yes, Sir. [She goes].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [eagerly, going to his mother] Genteel relatives! now we shall hear something. [He sits down in the Chippendale chair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Do you know any of her people?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Only her father: the fellow we told you about.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID [announcing] Mr. Doolittle. [She withdraws].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Doolittle enters. He is brilliantly dressed in a new fashionable frock-coat, with white waistcoat and grey trousers. A flower in his buttonhole, a dazzling silk hat, and patent leather shoes complete the effect. He is too concerned with the business he has come on to notice Mrs. Higgins. He walks straight to Higgins, and accosts him with vehement reproach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [indicating his own person] See here! Do you see this? You done this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Done what, man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. This, I tell you. Look at it. Look at this hat. Look at this coat.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Has Eliza been buying you clothes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Eliza! not she. Not half. Why would she buy me clothes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Good-morning, Mr. Doolittle. Won’t you sit down?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [taken aback as he becomes conscious that he has forgotten his hostess] Asking your pardon, ma’am. [He approaches her and shakes her proffered hand]. Thank you. [He sits down on the ottoman, on Pickering’s right]. I am that full of what has happened to me that I can’t think of anything else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What the dickens has happened to you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. I shouldn’t mind if it had only happened to me: anything might happen to anybody and nobody to blame but Providence, as you might say. But this is something that you done to me: yes, you, Henry Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Have you found Eliza? That’s the point.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Have you lost her?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. You have all the luck, you have. I ain’t found her; but she’ll find me quick enough now after what you done to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. But what has my son done to you, Mr. Doolittle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Done to me! Ruined me. Destroyed my happiness. Tied me up and delivered me into the hands of middle class morality.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising intolerantly and standing over Doolittle] You’re raving. You’re drunk. You’re mad. I gave you five pounds. After that I had two conversations with you, at half-a-crown an hour. I’ve never seen you since.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Oh! Drunk! am I? Mad! am I? Tell me this. Did you or did you not write a letter to an old blighter in America that was giving five millions to found Moral Reform Societies all over the world, and that wanted you to invent a universal language for him?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What! Ezra D. Wannafeller! He’s dead. [He sits down again carelessly].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Yes: he’s dead; and I’m done for. Now did you or did you not write a letter to him to say that the most original moralist at present in England, to the best of your knowledge, was Alfred Doolittle, a common dustman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, after your last visit I remember making some silly joke of the kind.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Ah! you may well call it a silly joke. It put the lid on me right enough. Just give him the chance he wanted to show that Americans is not like us: that they recognize and respect merit in every class of life, however humble. Them words is in his blooming will, in which, Henry Higgins, thanks to your silly joking, he leaves me a share in his Pre-digested Cheese Trust worth three thousand a year on condition that I lecture for his Wannafeller Moral Reform World League as often as they ask me up to six times a year.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. The devil he does! Whew! [Brightening suddenly] What a lark!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. A safe thing for you, Doolittle. They won’t ask you twice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. It ain’t the lecturing I mind. I’ll lecture them blue in the face, I will, and not turn a hair. It’s making a gentleman of me that I object to. Who asked him to make a gentleman of me? I was happy. I was free. I touched pretty nigh everybody for money when I wanted it, same as I touched you, Henry Higgins. Now I am worrited; tied neck and heels; and everybody touches me for money. It’s a fine thing for you, says my solicitor. Is it? says I. You mean it’s a good thing for you, I says. When I was a poor man and had a solicitor once when they found a pram in the dust cart, he got me off, and got shut of me and got me shut of him as quick as he could. Same with the doctors: used to shove me out of the hospital before I could hardly stand on my legs, and nothing to pay. Now they finds out that I’m not a healthy man and can’t live unless they looks after me twice a day. In the house I’m not let do a hand’s turn for myself: somebody else must do it and touch me for it. A year ago I hadn’t a relative in the world except two or three that wouldn’t speak to me. Now I’ve fifty, and not a decent week’s wages among the lot of them. I have to live for others and not for myself: that’s middle class morality. You talk of losing Eliza. Don’t you be anxious: I bet she’s on my doorstep by this: she that could support herself easy by selling flowers if I wasn’t respectable. And the next one to touch me will be you, Henry Higgins. I’ll have to learn to speak middle class language from you, instead of speaking proper English. That’s where you’ll come in; and I daresay that’s what you done it for.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. But, my dear Mr. Doolittle, you need not suffer all this if you are really in earnest. Nobody can force you to accept this bequest. You can repudiate it. Isn’t that so, Colonel Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. I believe so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [softening his manner in deference to her sex] That’s the tragedy of it, ma’am. It’s easy to say chuck it; but I haven’t the nerve. Which one of us has? We’re all intimidated. Intimidated, ma’am: that’s what we are. What is there for me if I chuck it but the workhouse in my old age? I have to dye my hair already to keep my job as a dustman. If I was one of the deserving poor, and had put by a bit, I could chuck it; but then why should I, acause the deserving poor might as well be millionaires for all the happiness they ever has. They don’t know what happiness is. But I, as one of the undeserving poor, have nothing between me and the pauper’s uniform but this here blasted three thousand a year that shoves me into the middle class. (Excuse the expression, ma’am: you’d use it yourself if you had my provocation). They’ve got you every way you turn: it’s a choice between the Skilly of the workhouse and the Char Bydis of the middle class; and I haven’t the nerve for the workhouse. Intimidated: that’s what I am. Broke. Bought up. Happier men than me will call for my dust, and touch me for their tip; and I’ll look on helpless, and envy them. And that’s what your son has brought me to. [He is overcome by emotion].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Well, I’m very glad you’re not going to do anything foolish, Mr. Doolittle. For this solves the problem of Eliza’s future. You can provide for her now.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [with melancholy resignation] Yes, ma’am; I’m expected to provide for everyone now, out of three thousand a year.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [jumping up] Nonsense! he can’t provide for her. He shan’t provide for her. She doesn’t belong to him. I paid him five pounds for her. Doolittle: either you’re an honest man or a rogue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [tolerantly] A little of both, Henry, like the rest of us: a little of both.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, you took that money for the girl; and you have no right to take her as well.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Henry: don’t be absurd. If you really want to know where Eliza is, she is upstairs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [amazed] Upstairs!!! Then I shall jolly soon fetch her downstairs. [He makes resolutely for the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [rising and following him] Be quiet, Henry. Sit down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Sit down, dear; and listen to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh very well, very well, very well. [He throws himself ungraciously on the ottoman, with his face towards the windows]. But I think you might have told me this half an hour ago.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Eliza came to me this morning. She passed the night partly walking about in a rage, partly trying to throw herself into the river and being afraid to, and partly in the Carlton Hotel. She told me of the brutal way you two treated her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [bounding up again] What!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [rising also] My dear Mrs. Higgins, she’s been telling you stories. We didn’t treat her brutally. We hardly said a word to her; and we parted on particularly good terms. [Turning on Higgins]. Higgins: did you bully her after I went to bed?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Just the other way about. She threw my slippers in my face. She behaved in the most outrageous way. I never gave her the slightest provocation. The slippers came bang into my face the moment I entered the room—before I had uttered a word. And used perfectly awful language.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [astonished] But why? What did we do to her?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. I think I know pretty well what you did. The girl is naturally rather affectionate, I think. Isn’t she, Mr. Doolittle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Very tender-hearted, ma’am. Takes after me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Just so. She had become attached to you both. She worked very hard for you, Henry! I don’t think you quite realize what anything in the nature of brain work means to a girl like that. Well, it seems that when the great day of trial came, and she did this wonderful thing for you without making a single mistake, you two sat there and never said a word to her, but talked together of how glad you were that it was all over and how you had been bored with the whole thing. And then you were surprised because she threw your slippers at you! <i>I</i> should have thrown the fire-irons at you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. We said nothing except that we were tired and wanted to go to bed. Did we, Pick?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [shrugging his shoulders] That was all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [ironically] Quite sure?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Absolutely. Really, that was all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. You didn’t thank her, or pet her, or admire her, or tell her how splendid she’d been.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [impatiently] But she knew all about that. We didn’t make speeches to her, if that’s what you mean.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [conscience stricken] Perhaps we were a little inconsiderate. Is she very angry?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [returning to her place at the writing-table] Well, I’m afraid she won’t go back to Wimpole Street, especially now that Mr. Doolittle is able to keep up the position you have thrust on her; but she says she is quite willing to meet you on friendly terms and to let bygones be bygones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [furious] Is she, by George? Ho!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. If you promise to behave yourself, Henry, I’ll ask her to come down. If not, go home; for you have taken up quite enough of my time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Oh, all right. Very well. Pick: you behave yourself. Let us put on our best Sunday manners for this creature that we picked out of the mud. [He flings himself sulkily into the Elizabethan chair].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [remonstrating] Now, now, Henry Higgins! have some consideration for my feelings as a middle class man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Remember your promise, Henry. [She presses the bell-button on the writing-table]. Mr. Doolittle: will you be so good as to step out on the balcony for a moment. I don’t want Eliza to have the shock of your news until she has made it up with these two gentlemen. Would you mind?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. As you wish, lady. Anything to help Henry to keep her off my hands. [He disappears through the window].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">The parlor-maid answers the bell. Pickering sits down in Doolittle’s place.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Ask Miss Doolittle to come down, please.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">THE PARLOR-MAID. Yes, mam. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Now, Henry: be good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I am behaving myself perfectly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. He is doing his best, Mrs. Higgins.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">A pause. Higgins throws back his head; stretches out his legs; and begins to whistle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Henry, dearest, you don’t look at all nice in that attitude.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [pulling himself together] I was not trying to look nice, mother.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. It doesn’t matter, dear. I only wanted to make you speak.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Why?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Because you can’t speak and whistle at the same time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins groans. Another very trying pause.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [springing up, out of patience] Where the devil is that girl? Are we to wait here all day?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza enters, sunny, self-possessed, and giving a staggeringly convincing exhibition of ease of manner. She carries a little work-basket, and is very much at home. Pickering is too much taken aback to rise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. How do you do, Professor Higgins? Are you quite well?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [choking] Am I— [He can say no more].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. But of course you are: you are never ill. So glad to see you again, Colonel Pickering. [He rises hastily; and they shake hands]. Quite chilly this morning, isn’t it? [She sits down on his left. He sits beside her].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Don’t you dare try this game on me. I taught it to you; and it doesn’t take me in. Get up and come home; and don’t be a fool.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza takes a piece of needlework from her basket, and begins to stitch at it, without taking the least notice of this outburst.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Very nicely put, indeed, Henry. No woman could resist such an invitation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You let her alone, mother. Let her speak for herself. You will jolly soon see whether she has an idea that I haven’t put into her head or a word that I haven’t put into her mouth. I tell you I have created this thing out of the squashed cabbage leaves of Covent Garden; and now she pretends to play the fine lady with me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [placidly] Yes, dear; but you’ll sit down, won’t you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Higgins sits down again, savagely.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [to Pickering, taking no apparent notice of Higgins, and working away deftly] Will you drop me altogether now that the experiment is over, Colonel Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh don’t. You mustn’t think of it as an experiment. It shocks me, somehow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, I’m only a squashed cabbage leaf.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [impulsively] No.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [continuing quietly]—but I owe so much to you that I should be very unhappy if you forgot me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. It’s very kind of you to say so, Miss Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. It’s not because you paid for my dresses. I know you are generous to everybody with money. But it was from you that I learnt really nice manners; and that is what makes one a lady, isn’t it? You see it was so very difficult for me with the example of Professor Higgins always before me. I was brought up to be just like him, unable to control myself, and using bad language on the slightest provocation. And I should never have known that ladies and gentlemen didn’t behave like that if you hadn’t been there.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well!!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh, that’s only his way, you know. He doesn’t mean it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, I didn’t mean it either, when I was a flower girl. It was only my way. But you see I did it; and that’s what makes the difference after all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. No doubt. Still, he taught you to speak; and I couldn’t have done that, you know.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [trivially] Of course: that is his profession.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Damnation!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [continuing] It was just like learning to dance in the fashionable way: there was nothing more than that in it. But do you know what began my real education?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. What?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [stopping her work for a moment] Your calling me Miss Doolittle that day when I first came to Wimpole Street. That was the beginning of self-respect for me. [She resumes her stitching]. And there were a hundred little things you never noticed, because they came naturally to you. Things about standing up and taking off your hat and opening doors—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Oh, that was nothing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Yes: things that showed you thought and felt about me as if I were something better than a scullery-maid; though of course I know you would have been just the same to a scullery-maid if she had been let in the drawing-room. You never took off your boots in the dining room when I was there.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. You mustn’t mind that. Higgins takes off his boots all over the place.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I know. I am not blaming him. It is his way, isn’t it? But it made such a difference to me that you didn’t do it. You see, really and truly, apart from the things anyone can pick up (the dressing and the proper way of speaking, and so on), the difference between a lady and a flower girl is not how she behaves, but how she’s treated. I shall always be a flower girl to Professor Higgins, because he always treats me as a flower girl, and always will; but I know I can be a lady to you, because you always treat me as a lady, and always will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Please don’t grind your teeth, Henry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Well, this is really very nice of you, Miss Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I should like you to call me Eliza, now, if you would.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Thank you. Eliza, of course.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. And I should like Professor Higgins to call me Miss Doolittle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I’ll see you damned first.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Henry! Henry!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [laughing] Why don’t you slang back at him? Don’t stand it. It would do him a lot of good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I can’t. I could have done it once; but now I can’t go back to it. Last night, when I was wandering about, a girl spoke to me; and I tried to get back into the old way with her; but it was no use. You told me, you know, that when a child is brought to a foreign country, it picks up the language in a few weeks, and forgets its own. Well, I am a child in your country. I have forgotten my own language, and can speak nothing but yours. That’s the real break-off with the corner of Tottenham Court Road. Leaving Wimpole Street finishes it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [much alarmed] Oh! but you’re coming back to Wimpole Street, aren’t you? You’ll forgive Higgins?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising] Forgive! Will she, by George! Let her go. Let her find out how she can get on without us. She will relapse into the gutter in three weeks without me at her elbow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Doolittle appears at the centre window. With a look of dignified reproach at Higgins, he comes slowly and silently to his daughter, who, with her back to the window, is unconscious of his approach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. He’s incorrigible, Eliza. You won’t relapse, will you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No: Not now. Never again. I have learnt my lesson. I don’t believe I could utter one of the old sounds if I tried. [Doolittle touches her on her left shoulder. She drops her work, losing her self-possession utterly at the spectacle of her father’s splendor] A—a—a—a—a—ah—ow—ooh!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [with a crow of triumph] Aha! Just so. A—a—a—a—ahowooh! A—a—a—a—ahowooh ! A—a—a—a—ahowooh! Victory! Victory! [He throws himself on the divan, folding his arms, and spraddling arrogantly].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Can you blame the girl? Don’t look at me like that, Eliza. It ain’t my fault. I’ve come into money.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You must have touched a millionaire this time, dad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. I have. But I’m dressed something special today. I’m going to St. George’s, Hanover Square. Your stepmother is going to marry me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [angrily] You’re going to let yourself down to marry that low common woman!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [quietly] He ought to, Eliza. [To Doolittle] Why has she changed her mind?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [sadly] Intimidated, Governor. Intimidated. Middle class morality claims its victim. Won’t you put on your hat, Liza, and come and see me turned off?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. If the Colonel says I must, I—I’ll [almost sobbing] I’ll demean myself. And get insulted for my pains, like enough.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000000999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Don’t be afraid: she never comes to words with anyone now, poor woman! respectability has broke all the spirit out of her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [squeezing Eliza’s elbow gently] Be kind to them, Eliza. Make the best of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [forcing a little smile for him through her vexation] Oh well, just to show there’s no ill feeling. I’ll be back in a moment. [She goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [sitting down beside Pickering] I feel uncommon nervous about the ceremony, Colonel. I wish you’d come and see me through it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. But you’ve been through it before, man. You were married to Eliza’s mother.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Who told you that, Colonel?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Well, nobody told me. But I concluded naturally—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. No: that ain’t the natural way, Colonel: it’s only the middle class way. My way was always the undeserving way. But don’t say nothing to Eliza. She don’t know: I always had a delicacy about telling her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Quite right. We’ll leave it so, if you don’t mind.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. And you’ll come to the church, Colonel, and put me through straight?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. With pleasure. As far as a bachelor can.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. May I come, Mr. Doolittle? I should be very sorry to miss your wedding.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. I should indeed be honored by your condescension, ma’am; and my poor old woman would take it as a tremenjous compliment. She’s been very low, thinking of the happy days that are no more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [rising] I’ll order the carriage and get ready. [The men rise, except Higgins]. I shan’t be more than fifteen minutes. [As she goes to the door Eliza comes in, hatted and buttoning her gloves]. I’m going to the church to see your father married, Eliza. You had better come in the brougham with me. Colonel Pickering can go on with the bridegroom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Higgins goes out. Eliza comes to the middle of the room between the centre window and the ottoman. Pickering joins her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE. Bridegroom! What a word! It makes a man realize his position, somehow. [He takes up his hat and goes towards the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING. Before I go, Eliza, do forgive him and come back to us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I don’t think papa would allow me. Would you, dad?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">DOOLITTLE [sad but magnanimous] They played you off very cunning, Eliza, them two sportsmen. If it had been only one of them, you could have nailed him. But you see, there was two; and one of them chaperoned the other, as you might say. [To Pickering] It was artful of you, Colonel; but I bear no malice: I should have done the same myself. I been the victim of one woman after another all my life; and I don’t grudge you two getting the better of Eliza. I shan’t interfere. It’s time for us to go, Colonel. So long, Henry. See you in St. George’s, Eliza. [He goes out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">PICKERING [coaxing] Do stay with us, Eliza. [He follows Doolittle].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Eliza goes out on the balcony to avoid being alone with Higgins. He rises and joins her there. She immediately comes back into the room and makes for the door; but he goes along the balcony quickly and gets his back to the door before she reaches it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, Eliza, you’ve had a bit of your own back, as you call it. Have you had enough? and are you going to be reasonable? Or do you want any more?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You want me back only to pick up your slippers and put up with your tempers and fetch and carry for you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I haven’t said I wanted you back at all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, indeed. Then what are we talking about?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. About you, not about me. If you come back I shall treat you just as I have always treated you. I can’t change my nature; and I don’t intend to change my manners. My manners are exactly the same as Colonel Pickering’s.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. That’s not true. He treats a flower girl as if she was a duchess.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. And I treat a duchess as if she was a flower girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I see. [She turns away composedly, and sits on the ottoman, facing the window]. The same to everybody.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Just so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Like father.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [grinning, a little taken down] Without accepting the comparison at all points, Eliza, it’s quite true that your father is not a snob, and that he will be quite at home in any station of life to which his eccentric destiny may call him. [Seriously] The great secret, Eliza, is not having bad manners or good manners or any other particular sort of manners, but having the same manner for all human souls: in short, behaving as if you were in Heaven, where there are no third-class carriages, and one soul is as good as another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Amen. You are a born preacher.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [irritated] The question is not whether I treat you rudely, but whether you ever heard me treat anyone else better.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [with sudden sincerity] I don’t care how you treat me. I don’t mind your swearing at me. I don’t mind a black eye: I’ve had one before this. But [standing up and facing him] I won’t be passed over.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Then get out of my way; for I won’t stop for you. You talk about me as if I were a motor bus.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. So you are a motor bus: all bounce and go, and no consideration for anyone. But I can do without you: don’t think I can’t.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I know you can. I told you you could.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [wounded, getting away from him to the other side of the ottoman with her face to the hearth] I know you did, you brute. You wanted to get rid of me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Liar.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Thank you. [She sits down with dignity].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. You never asked yourself, I suppose, whether I could do without YOU.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [earnestly] Don’t you try to get round me. You’ll HAVE to do without me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [arrogant] I can do without anybody. I have my own soul: my own spark of divine fire. But [with sudden humility] I shall miss you, Eliza. [He sits down near her on the ottoman]. I have learnt something from your idiotic notions: I confess that humbly and gratefully. And I have grown accustomed to your voice and appearance. I like them, rather.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Well, you have both of them on your gramophone and in your book of photographs. When you feel lonely without me, you can turn the machine on. It’s got no feelings to hurt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I can’t turn your soul on. Leave me those feelings; and you can take away the voice and the face. They are not you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh, you ARE a devil. You can twist the heart in a girl as easy as some could twist her arms to hurt her. Mrs. Pearce warned me. Time and again she has wanted to leave you; and you always got round her at the last minute. And you don’t care a bit for her. And you don’t care a bit for me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I care for life, for humanity; and you are a part of it that has come my way and been built into my house. What more can you or anyone ask?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I won’t care for anybody that doesn’t care for me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Commercial principles, Eliza. Like [reproducing her Covent Garden pronunciation with professional exactness] s’yollin voylets [selling violets], isn’t it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Don’t sneer at me. It’s mean to sneer at me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. I have never sneered in my life. Sneering doesn’t become either the human face or the human soul. I am expressing my righteous contempt for Commercialism. I don’t and won’t trade in affection. You call me a brute because you couldn’t buy a claim on me by fetching my slippers and finding my spectacles. You were a fool: I think a woman fetching a man’s slippers is a disgusting sight: did I ever fetch YOUR slippers? I think a good deal more of you for throwing them in my face. No use slaving for me and then saying you want to be cared for: who cares for a slave? If you come back, come back for the sake of good fellowship; for you’ll get nothing else. You’ve had a thousand times as much out of me as I have out of you; and if you dare to set up your little dog’s tricks of fetching and carrying slippers against my creation of a Duchess Eliza, I’ll slam the door in your silly face.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What did you do it for if you didn’t care for me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [heartily] Why, because it was my job.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You never thought of the trouble it would make for me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Would the world ever have been made if its maker had been afraid of making trouble? Making life means making trouble. There’s only one way of escaping trouble; and that’s killing things. Cowards, you notice, are always shrieking to have troublesome people killed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I’m no preacher: I don’t notice things like that. I notice that you don’t notice me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [jumping up and walking about intolerantly] Eliza: you’re an idiot. I waste the treasures of my Miltonic mind by spreading them before you. Once for all, understand that I go my way and do my work without caring twopence what happens to either of us. I am not intimidated, like your father and your stepmother. So you can come back or go to the devil: which you please.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What am I to come back for?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [bouncing up on his knees on the ottoman and leaning over it to her] For the fun of it. That’s why I took you on.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [with averted face] And you may throw me out tomorrow if I don’t do everything you want me to?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes; and you may walk out tomorrow if I don’t do everything YOU want me to.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. And live with my stepmother?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Yes, or sell flowers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Oh! if I only COULD go back to my flower basket! I should be independent of both you and father and all the world! Why did you take my independence from me? Why did I give it up? I’m a slave now, for all my fine clothes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Not a bit. I’ll adopt you as my daughter and settle money on you if you like. Or would you rather marry Pickering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [looking fiercely round at him] I wouldn’t marry YOU if you asked me; and you’re nearer my age than what he is.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [gently] Than he is: not “than what he is.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [losing her temper and rising] I’ll talk as I like. You’re not my teacher now.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [reflectively] I don’t suppose Pickering would, though. He’s as confirmed an old bachelor as I am.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. That’s not what I want; and don’t you think it. I’ve always had chaps enough wanting me that way. Freddy Hill writes to me twice and three times a day, sheets and sheets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [disagreeably surprised] Damn his impudence! [He recoils and finds himself sitting on his heels].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. He has a right to if he likes, poor lad. And he does love me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [getting off the ottoman] You have no right to encourage him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Every girl has a right to be loved.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What! By fools like that?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Freddy’s not a fool. And if he’s weak and poor and wants me, may be he’d make me happier than my betters that bully me and don’t want me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Can he MAKE anything of you? That’s the point.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Perhaps I could make something of him. But I never thought of us making anything of one another; and you never think of anything else. I only want to be natural.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. In short, you want me to be as infatuated about you as Freddy? Is that it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. No I don’t. That’s not the sort of feeling I want from you. And don’t you be too sure of yourself or of me. I could have been a bad girl if I’d liked. I’ve seen more of some things than you, for all your learning. Girls like me can drag gentlemen down to make love to them easy enough. And they wish each other dead the next minute.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Of course they do. Then what in thunder are we quarrelling about?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [much troubled] I want a little kindness. I know I’m a common ignorant girl, and you a book-learned gentleman; but I’m not dirt under your feet. What I done [correcting herself] what I did was not for the dresses and the taxis: I did it because we were pleasant together and I come—came—to care for you; not to want you to make love to me, and not forgetting the difference between us, but more friendly like.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Well, of course. That’s just how I feel. And how Pickering feels. Eliza: you’re a fool.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. That’s not a proper answer to give me [she sinks on the chair at the writing-table in tears].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. It’s all you’ll get until you stop being a common idiot. If you’re going to be a lady, you’ll have to give up feeling neglected if the men you know don’t spend half their time snivelling over you and the other half giving you black eyes. If you can’t stand the coldness of my sort of life, and the strain of it, go back to the gutter. Work til you are more a brute than a human being; and then cuddle and squabble and drink til you fall asleep. Oh, it’s a fine life, the life of the gutter. It’s real: it’s warm: it’s violent: you can feel it through the thickest skin: you can taste it and smell it without any training or any work. Not like Science and Literature and Classical Music and Philosophy and Art. You find me cold, unfeeling, selfish, don’t you? Very well: be off with you to the sort of people you like. Marry some sentimental hog or other with lots of money, and a thick pair of lips to kiss you with and a thick pair of boots to kick you with. If you can’t appreciate what you’ve got, you’d better get what you can appreciate.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [desperate] Oh, you are a cruel tyrant. I can’t talk to you: you turn everything against me: I’m always in the wrong. But you know very well all the time that you’re nothing but a bully. You know I can’t go back to the gutter, as you call it, and that I have no real friends in the world but you and the Colonel. You know well I couldn’t bear to live with a low common man after you two; and it’s wicked and cruel of you to insult me by pretending I could. You think I must go back to Wimpole Street because I have nowhere else to go but father’s. But don’t you be too sure that you have me under your feet to be trampled on and talked down. I’ll marry Freddy, I will, as soon as he’s able to support me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [sitting down beside her] Rubbish! you shall marry an ambassador. You shall marry the Governor-General of India or the Lord-Lieutenant of Ireland, or somebody who wants a deputy-queen. I’m not going to have my masterpiece thrown away on Freddy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. You think I like you to say that. But I haven’t forgot what you said a minute ago; and I won’t be coaxed round as if I was a baby or a puppy. If I can’t have kindness, I’ll have independence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Independence? That’s middle class blasphemy. We are all dependent on one another, every soul of us on earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [rising determinedly] I’ll let you see whether I’m dependent on you. If you can preach, I can teach. I’ll go and be a teacher.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. What’ll you teach, in heaven’s name?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. What you taught me. I’ll teach phonetics.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Ha! Ha! Ha!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. I’ll offer myself as an assistant to Professor Nepean.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [rising in a fury] What! That impostor! that humbug! that toadying ignoramus! Teach him my methods! my discoveries! You take one step in his direction and I’ll wring your neck. [He lays hands on her]. Do you hear?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [defiantly non-resistant] Wring away. What do I care? I knew you’d strike me some day. [He lets her go, stamping with rage at having forgotten himself, and recoils so hastily that he stumbles back into his seat on the ottoman]. Aha! Now I know how to deal with you. What a fool I was not to think of it before! You can’t take away the knowledge you gave me. You said I had a finer ear than you. And I can be civil and kind to people, which is more than you can. Aha! That’s done you, Henry Higgins, it has. Now I don’t care that [snapping her fingers] for your bullying and your big talk. I’ll advertize it in the papers that your duchess is only a flower girl that you taught, and that she’ll teach anybody to be a duchess just the same in six months for a thousand guineas. Oh, when I think of myself crawling under your feet and being trampled on and called names, when all the time I had only to lift up my finger to be as good as you, I could just kick myself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [wondering at her] You damned impudent slut, you! But it’s better than snivelling; better than fetching slippers and finding spectacles, isn’t it? [Rising] By George, Eliza, I said I’d make a woman of you; and I have. I like you like this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Yes: you turn round and make up to me now that I’m not afraid of you, and can do without you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Of course I do, you little fool. Five minutes ago you were like a millstone round my neck. Now you’re a tower of strength: a consort battleship. You and I and Pickering will be three old bachelors together instead of only two men and a silly girl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">Mrs. Higgins returns, dressed for the wedding. Eliza instantly becomes cool and elegant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. The carriage is waiting, Eliza. Are you ready?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Quite. Is the Professor coming?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. Certainly not. He can’t behave himself in church. He makes remarks out loud all the time on the clergyman’s pronunciation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA. Then I shall not see you again, Professor. Good bye. [She goes to the door].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS [coming to Higgins] Good-bye, dear.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS. Good-bye, mother. [He is about to kiss her, when he recollects something]. Oh, by the way, Eliza, order a ham and a Stilton cheese, will you? And buy me a pair of reindeer gloves, number eights, and a tie to match that new suit of mine, at Eale &amp; Binman’s. You can choose the color. [His cheerful, careless, vigorous voice shows that he is incorrigible].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">LIZA [disdainfully] Buy them yourself. [She sweeps out].</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">MRS. HIGGINS. I’m afraid you’ve spoiled that girl, Henry. But never mind, dear: I’ll buy you the tie and gloves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"dialog\">HIGGINS [sunnily] Oh, don’t bother. She’ll buy em all right enough. Good-bye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p class=\"stage\">They kiss. Mrs. Higgins runs out. Higgins, left alone, rattles his cash in his pocket; chuckles; and disports himself in a highly self-satisfied manner.<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p><br>\n<br>\nThe rest of the story need not be shown in action, and indeed, would hardly need telling if our imaginations were not so enfeebled by their lazy dependence on the ready-makes and reach-me-downs of the ragshop in which Romance keeps its stock of “happy endings” to misfit all stories. Now, the history of Eliza Doolittle, though called a romance because of the transfiguration it records seems exceedingly improbable, is common enough. Such transfigurations have been achieved by hundreds of resolutely ambitious young women since Nell Gwynne set them the example by playing queens and fascinating kings in the theatre in which she began by selling oranges. Nevertheless, people in all directions have assumed, for no other reason than that she became the heroine of a romance, that she must have married the hero of it. This is unbearable, not only because her little drama, if acted on such a thoughtless assumption, must be spoiled, but because the true sequel is patent to anyone with a sense of human nature in general, and of feminine instinct in particular.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Eliza, in telling Higgins she would not marry him if he asked her, was not coquetting: she was announcing a well-considered decision. When a bachelor interests, and dominates, and teaches, and becomes important to a spinster, as Higgins with Eliza, she always, if she has character enough to be capable of it, considers very seriously indeed whether she will play for becoming that bachelor’s wife, especially if he is so little interested in marriage that a determined and devoted woman might capture him if she set herself resolutely to do it. Her decision will depend a good deal on whether she is really free to choose; and that, again, will depend on her age and income. If she is at the end of her youth, and has no security for her livelihood, she will marry him because she must marry anybody who will provide for her. But at Eliza’s age a good-looking girl does not feel that pressure; she feels free to pick and choose. She is therefore guided by her instinct in the matter. Eliza’s instinct tells her not to marry Higgins. It does not tell her to give him up. It is not in the slightest doubt as to his remaining one of the strongest personal interests in her life. It would be very sorely strained if there was another woman likely to supplant her with him. But as she feels sure of him on that last point, she has no doubt at all as to her course, and would not have any, even if the difference of twenty years in age, which seems so great to youth, did not exist between them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>As our own instincts are not appealed to by her conclusion, let us see whether we cannot discover some reason in it. When Higgins excused his indifference to young women on the ground that they had an irresistible rival in his mother, he gave the clue to his inveterate old-bachelordom. The case is uncommon only to the extent that remarkable mothers are uncommon. If an imaginative boy has a sufficiently rich mother who has intelligence, personal grace, dignity of character without harshness, and a cultivated sense of the best art of her time to enable her to make her house beautiful, she sets a standard for him against which very few women can struggle, besides effecting for him a disengagement of his affections, his sense of beauty, and his idealism from his specifically sexual impulses. This makes him a standing puzzle to the huge number of uncultivated people who have been brought up in tasteless homes by commonplace or disagreeable parents, and to whom, consequently, literature, painting, sculpture, music, and affectionate personal relations come as modes of sex if they come at all. The word passion means nothing else to them; and that Higgins could have a passion for phonetics and idealize his mother instead of Eliza, would seem to them absurd and unnatural. Nevertheless, when we look round and see that hardly anyone is too ugly or disagreeable to find a wife or a husband if he or she wants one, whilst many old maids and bachelors are above the average in quality and culture, we cannot help suspecting that the disentanglement of sex from the associations with which it is so commonly confused, a disentanglement which persons of genius achieve by sheer intellectual analysis, is sometimes produced or aided by parental fascination.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, though Eliza was incapable of thus explaining to herself Higgins’s formidable powers of resistance to the charm that prostrated Freddy at the first glance, she was instinctively aware that she could never obtain a complete grip of him, or come between him and his mother (the first necessity of the married woman). To put it shortly, she knew that for some mysterious reason he had not the makings of a married man in him, according to her conception of a husband as one to whom she would be his nearest and fondest and warmest interest. Even had there been no mother-rival, she would still have refused to accept an interest in herself that was secondary to philosophic interests. Had Mrs. Higgins died, there would still have been Milton and the Universal Alphabet. Landor’s remark that to those who have the greatest power of loving, love is a secondary affair, would not have recommended Landor to Eliza. Put that along with her resentment of Higgins’s domineering superiority, and her mistrust of his coaxing cleverness in getting round her and evading her wrath when he had gone too far with his impetuous bullying, and you will see that Eliza’s instinct had good grounds for warning her not to marry her Pygmalion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>And now, whom did Eliza marry? For if Higgins was a predestinate old bachelor, she was most certainly not a predestinate old maid. Well, that can be told very shortly to those who have not guessed it from the indications she has herself given them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Almost immediately after Eliza is stung into proclaiming her considered determination not to marry Higgins, she mentions the fact that young Mr. Frederick Eynsford Hill is pouring out his love for her daily through the post. Now Freddy is young, practically twenty years younger than Higgins: he is a gentleman (or, as Eliza would qualify him, a toff), and speaks like one; he is nicely dressed, is treated by the Colonel as an equal, loves her unaffectedly, and is not her master, nor ever likely to dominate her in spite of his advantage of social standing. Eliza has no use for the foolish romantic tradition that all women love to be mastered, if not actually bullied and beaten. “When you go to women,” says Nietzsche, “take your whip with you.” Sensible despots have never confined that precaution to women: they have taken their whips with them when they have dealt with men, and been slavishly idealized by the men over whom they have flourished the whip much more than by women. No doubt there are slavish women as well as slavish men; and women, like men, admire those that are stronger than themselves. But to admire a strong person and to live under that strong person’s thumb are two different things. The weak may not be admired and hero-worshipped; but they are by no means disliked or shunned; and they never seem to have the least difficulty in marrying people who are too good for them. They may fail in emergencies; but life is not one long emergency: it is mostly a string of situations for which no exceptional strength is needed, and with which even rather weak people can cope if they have a stronger partner to help them out. Accordingly, it is a truth everywhere in evidence that strong people, masculine or feminine, not only do not marry stronger people, but do not show any preference for them in selecting their friends. When a lion meets another with a louder roar “the first lion thinks the last a bore.” The man or woman who feels strong enough for two, seeks for every other quality in a partner than strength.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>The converse is also true. Weak people want to marry strong people who do not frighten them too much; and this often leads them to make the mistake we describe metaphorically as “biting off more than they can chew.” They want too much for too little; and when the bargain is unreasonable beyond all bearing, the union becomes impossible: it ends in the weaker party being either discarded or borne as a cross, which is worse. People who are not only weak, but silly or obtuse as well, are often in these difficulties.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>This being the state of human affairs, what is Eliza fairly sure to do when she is placed between Freddy and Higgins? Will she look forward to a lifetime of fetching Higgins’s slippers or to a lifetime of Freddy fetching hers? There can be no doubt about the answer. Unless Freddy is biologically repulsive to her, and Higgins biologically attractive to a degree that overwhelms all her other instincts, she will, if she marries either of them, marry Freddy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>And that is just what Eliza did.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Complications ensued; but they were economic, not romantic. Freddy had no money and no occupation. His mother’s jointure, a last relic of the opulence of Largelady Park, had enabled her to struggle along in Earlscourt with an air of gentility, but not to procure any serious secondary education for her children, much less give the boy a profession. A clerkship at thirty shillings a week was beneath Freddy’s dignity, and extremely distasteful to him besides. His prospects consisted of a hope that if he kept up appearances somebody would do something for him. The something appeared vaguely to his imagination as a private secretaryship or a sinecure of some sort. To his mother it perhaps appeared as a marriage to some lady of means who could not resist her boy’s niceness. Fancy her feelings when he married a flower girl who had become declassee under extraordinary circumstances which were now notorious!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>It is true that Eliza’s situation did not seem wholly ineligible. Her father, though formerly a dustman, and now fantastically disclassed, had become extremely popular in the smartest society by a social talent which triumphed over every prejudice and every disadvantage. Rejected by the middle class, which he loathed, he had shot up at once into the highest circles by his wit, his dustmanship (which he carried like a banner), and his Nietzschean transcendence of good and evil. At intimate ducal dinners he sat on the right hand of the Duchess; and in country houses he smoked in the pantry and was made much of by the butler when he was not feeding in the dining-room and being consulted by cabinet ministers. But he found it almost as hard to do all this on four thousand a year as Mrs. Eynsford Hill to live in Earlscourt on an income so pitiably smaller that I have not the heart to disclose its exact figure. He absolutely refused to add the last straw to his burden by contributing to Eliza’s support.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus Freddy and Eliza, now Mr. and Mrs. Eynsford Hill, would have spent a penniless honeymoon but for a wedding present of 500 pounds from the Colonel to Eliza. It lasted a long time because Freddy did not know how to spend money, never having had any to spend, and Eliza, socially trained by a pair of old bachelors, wore her clothes as long as they held together and looked pretty, without the least regard to their being many months out of fashion. Still, 500 pounds will not last two young people for ever; and they both knew, and Eliza felt as well, that they must shift for themselves in the end. She could quarter herself on Wimpole Street because it had come to be her home; but she was quite aware that she ought not to quarter Freddy there, and that it would not be good for his character if she did.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Not that the Wimpole Street bachelors objected. When she consulted them, Higgins declined to be bothered about her housing problem when that solution was so simple. Eliza’s desire to have Freddy in the house with her seemed of no more importance than if she had wanted an extra piece of bedroom furniture. Pleas as to Freddy’s character, and the moral obligation on him to earn his own living, were lost on Higgins. He denied that Freddy had any character, and declared that if he tried to do any useful work some competent person would have the trouble of undoing it: a procedure involving a net loss to the community, and great unhappiness to Freddy himself, who was obviously intended by Nature for such light work as amusing Eliza, which, Higgins declared, was a much more useful and honorable occupation than working in the city. When Eliza referred again to her project of teaching phonetics, Higgins abated not a jot of his violent opposition to it. He said she was not within ten years of being qualified to meddle with his pet subject; and as it was evident that the Colonel agreed with him, she felt she could not go against them in this grave matter, and that she had no right, without Higgins’s consent, to exploit the knowledge he had given her; for his knowledge seemed to her as much his private property as his watch: Eliza was no communist. Besides, she was superstitiously devoted to them both, more entirely and frankly after her marriage than before it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>It was the Colonel who finally solved the problem, which had cost him much perplexed cogitation. He one day asked Eliza, rather shyly, whether she had quite given up her notion of keeping a flower shop. She replied that she had thought of it, but had put it out of her head, because the Colonel had said, that day at Mrs. Higgins’s, that it would never do. The Colonel confessed that when he said that, he had not quite recovered from the dazzling impression of the day before. They broke the matter to Higgins that evening. The sole comment vouchsafed by him very nearly led to a serious quarrel with Eliza. It was to the effect that she would have in Freddy an ideal errand boy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Freddy himself was next sounded on the subject. He said he had been thinking of a shop himself; though it had presented itself to his pennilessness as a small place in which Eliza should sell tobacco at one counter whilst he sold newspapers at the opposite one. But he agreed that it would be extraordinarily jolly to go early every morning with Eliza to Covent Garden and buy flowers on the scene of their first meeting: a sentiment which earned him many kisses from his wife. He added that he had always been afraid to propose anything of the sort, because Clara would make an awful row about a step that must damage her matrimonial chances, and his mother could not be expected to like it after clinging for so many years to that step of the social ladder on which retail trade is impossible.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>This difficulty was removed by an event highly unexpected by Freddy’s mother. Clara, in the course of her incursions into those artistic circles which were the highest within her reach, discovered that her conversational qualifications were expected to include a grounding in the novels of Mr. H.G. Wells. She borrowed them in various directions so energetically that she swallowed them all within two months. The result was a conversion of a kind quite common today. A modern Acts of the Apostles would fill fifty whole Bibles if anyone were capable of writing it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Poor Clara, who appeared to Higgins and his mother as a disagreeable and ridiculous person, and to her own mother as in some inexplicable way a social failure, had never seen herself in either light; for, though to some extent ridiculed and mimicked in West Kensington like everybody else there, she was accepted as a rational and normal—or shall we say inevitable?—sort of human being. At worst they called her The Pusher; but to them no more than to herself had it ever occurred that she was pushing the air, and pushing it in a wrong direction. Still, she was not happy. She was growing desperate. Her one asset, the fact that her mother was what the Epsom greengrocer called a carriage lady had no exchange value, apparently. It had prevented her from getting educated, because the only education she could have afforded was education with the Earlscourt green grocer’s daughter. It had led her to seek the society of her mother’s class; and that class simply would not have her, because she was much poorer than the greengrocer, and, far from being able to afford a maid, could not afford even a housemaid, and had to scrape along at home with an illiberally treated general servant. Under such circumstances nothing could give her an air of being a genuine product of Largelady Park. And yet its tradition made her regard a marriage with anyone within her reach as an unbearable humiliation. Commercial people and professional people in a small way were odious to her. She ran after painters and novelists; but she did not charm them; and her bold attempts to pick up and practise artistic and literary talk irritated them. She was, in short, an utter failure, an ignorant, incompetent, pretentious, unwelcome, penniless, useless little snob; and though she did not admit these disqualifications (for nobody ever faces unpleasant truths of this kind until the possibility of a way out dawns on them) she felt their effects too keenly to be satisfied with her position.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Clara had a startling eyeopener when, on being suddenly wakened to enthusiasm by a girl of her own age who dazzled her and produced in her a gushing desire to take her for a model, and gain her friendship, she discovered that this exquisite apparition had graduated from the gutter in a few months’ time. It shook her so violently, that when Mr. H. G. Wells lifted her on the point of his puissant pen, and placed her at the angle of view from which the life she was leading and the society to which she clung appeared in its true relation to real human needs and worthy social structure, he effected a conversion and a conviction of sin comparable to the most sensational feats of General Booth or Gypsy Smith. Clara’s snobbery went bang. Life suddenly began to move with her. Without knowing how or why, she began to make friends and enemies. Some of the acquaintances to whom she had been a tedious or indifferent or ridiculous affliction, dropped her: others became cordial. To her amazement she found that some “quite nice” people were saturated with Wells, and that this accessibility to ideas was the secret of their niceness. People she had thought deeply religious, and had tried to conciliate on that tack with disastrous results, suddenly took an interest in her, and revealed a hostility to conventional religion which she had never conceived possible except among the most desperate characters. They made her read Galsworthy; and Galsworthy exposed the vanity of Largelady Park and finished her. It exasperated her to think that the dungeon in which she had languished for so many unhappy years had been unlocked all the time, and that the impulses she had so carefully struggled with and stifled for the sake of keeping well with society, were precisely those by which alone she could have come into any sort of sincere human contact. In the radiance of these discoveries, and the tumult of their reaction, she made a fool of herself as freely and conspicuously as when she so rashly adopted Eliza’s expletive in Mrs. Higgins’s drawing-room; for the new-born Wellsian had to find her bearings almost as ridiculously as a baby; but nobody hates a baby for its ineptitudes, or thinks the worse of it for trying to eat the matches; and Clara lost no friends by her follies. They laughed at her to her face this time; and she had to defend herself and fight it out as best she could.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>When Freddy paid a visit to Earlscourt (which he never did when he could possibly help it) to make the desolating announcement that he and his Eliza were thinking of blackening the Largelady scutcheon by opening a shop, he found the little household already convulsed by a prior announcement from Clara that she also was going to work in an old furniture shop in Dover Street, which had been started by a fellow Wellsian. This appointment Clara owed, after all, to her old social accomplishment of Push. She had made up her mind that, cost what it might, she would see Mr. Wells in the flesh; and she had achieved her end at a garden party. She had better luck than so rash an enterprise deserved. Mr. Wells came up to her expectations. Age had not withered him, nor could custom stale his infinite variety in half an hour. His pleasant neatness and compactness, his small hands and feet, his teeming ready brain, his unaffected accessibility, and a certain fine apprehensiveness which stamped him as susceptible from his topmost hair to his tipmost toe, proved irresistible. Clara talked of nothing else for weeks and weeks afterwards. And as she happened to talk to the lady of the furniture shop, and that lady also desired above all things to know Mr. Wells and sell pretty things to him, she offered Clara a job on the chance of achieving that end through her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>And so it came about that Eliza’s luck held, and the expected opposition to the flower shop melted away. The shop is in the arcade of a railway station not very far from the Victoria and Albert Museum; and if you live in that neighborhood you may go there any day and buy a buttonhole from Eliza.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Now here is a last opportunity for romance. Would you not like to be assured that the shop was an immense success, thanks to Eliza’s charms and her early business experience in Covent Garden? Alas! the truth is the truth: the shop did not pay for a long time, simply because Eliza and her Freddy did not know how to keep it. True, Eliza had not to begin at the very beginning: she knew the names and prices of the cheaper flowers; and her elation was unbounded when she found that Freddy, like all youths educated at cheap, pretentious, and thoroughly inefficient schools, knew a little Latin. It was very little, but enough to make him appear to her a Porson or Bentley, and to put him at his ease with botanical nomenclature. Unfortunately he knew nothing else; and Eliza, though she could count money up to eighteen shillings or so, and had acquired a certain familiarity with the language of Milton from her struggles to qualify herself for winning Higgins’s bet, could not write out a bill without utterly disgracing the establishment. Freddy’s power of stating in Latin that Balbus built a wall and that Gaul was divided into three parts did not carry with it the slightest knowledge of accounts or business: Colonel Pickering had to explain to him what a cheque book and a bank account meant. And the pair were by no means easily teachable. Freddy backed up Eliza in her obstinate refusal to believe that they could save money by engaging a bookkeeper with some knowledge of the business. How, they argued, could you possibly save money by going to extra expense when you already could not make both ends meet? But the Colonel, after making the ends meet over and over again, at last gently insisted; and Eliza, humbled to the dust by having to beg from him so often, and stung by the uproarious derision of Higgins, to whom the notion of Freddy succeeding at anything was a joke that never palled, grasped the fact that business, like phonetics, has to be learned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>On the piteous spectacle of the pair spending their evenings in shorthand schools and polytechnic classes, learning bookkeeping and typewriting with incipient junior clerks, male and female, from the elementary schools, let me not dwell. There were even classes at the London School of Economics, and a humble personal appeal to the director of that institution to recommend a course bearing on the flower business. He, being a humorist, explained to them the method of the celebrated Dickensian essay on Chinese Metaphysics by the gentleman who read an article on China and an article on Metaphysics and combined the information. He suggested that they should combine the London School with Kew Gardens. Eliza, to whom the procedure of the Dickensian gentleman seemed perfectly correct (as in fact it was) and not in the least funny (which was only her ignorance) took his advice with entire gravity. But the effort that cost her the deepest humiliation was a request to Higgins, whose pet artistic fancy, next to Milton’s verse, was calligraphy, and who himself wrote a most beautiful Italian hand, that he would teach her to write. He declared that she was congenitally incapable of forming a single letter worthy of the least of Milton’s words; but she persisted; and again he suddenly threw himself into the task of teaching her with a combination of stormy intensity, concentrated patience, and occasional bursts of interesting disquisition on the beauty and nobility, the august mission and destiny, of human handwriting. Eliza ended by acquiring an extremely uncommercial script which was a positive extension of her personal beauty, and spending three times as much on stationery as anyone else because certain qualities and shapes of paper became indispensable to her. She could not even address an envelope in the usual way because it made the margins all wrong.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>Their commercial school days were a period of disgrace and despair for the young couple. They seemed to be learning nothing about flower shops. At last they gave it up as hopeless, and shook the dust of the shorthand schools, and the polytechnics, and the London School of Economics from their feet for ever. Besides, the business was in some mysterious way beginning to take care of itself. They had somehow forgotten their objections to employing other people. They came to the conclusion that their own way was the best, and that they had really a remarkable talent for business. The Colonel, who had been compelled for some years to keep a sufficient sum on current account at his bankers to make up their deficits, found that the provision was unnecessary: the young people were prospering. It is true that there was not quite fair play between them and their competitors in trade. Their week-ends in the country cost them nothing, and saved them the price of their Sunday dinners; for the motor car was the Colonel’s; and he and Higgins paid the hotel bills. Mr. F. Hill, florist and greengrocer (they soon discovered that there was money in asparagus; and asparagus led to other vegetables), had an air which stamped the business as classy; and in private life he was still Frederick Eynsford Hill, Esquire. Not that there was any swank about him: nobody but Eliza knew that he had been christened Frederick Challoner. Eliza herself swanked like anything.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/31907291fa4b4d31/text/000001134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-2ab9e2 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-65abb9 twpub-31907291fa4b4d31-6b4cd0\"><p>That is all. That is how it has turned out. It is astonishing how much Eliza still manages to meddle in the housekeeping at Wimpole Street in spite of the shop and her own family. And it is notable that though she never nags her husband, and frankly loves the Colonel as if she were his favorite daughter, she has never got out of the habit of nagging Higgins that was established on the fatal night when she won his bet for him. She snaps his head off on the faintest provocation, or on none. He no longer dares to tease her by assuming an abysmal inferiority of Freddy’s mind to his own. He storms and bullies and derides; but she stands up to him so ruthlessly that the Colonel has to ask her from time to time to be kinder to Higgins; and it is the only request of his that brings a mulish expression into her face. Nothing but some emergency or calamity great enough to break down all likes and dislikes, and throw them both back on their common humanity—and may they be spared any such trial!—will ever alter this. She knows that Higgins does not need her, just as her father did not need her. The very scrupulousness with which he told her that day that he had become used to having her there, and dependent on her for all sorts of little services, and that he should miss her if she went away (it would never have occurred to Freddy or the Colonel to say anything of the sort) deepens her inner certainty that she is “no more to him than them slippers”, yet she has a sense, too, that his indifference is deeper than the infatuation of commoner souls. She is immensely interested in him. She has even secret mischievous moments in which she wishes she could get him alone, on a desert island, away from all ties and with nobody else in the world to consider, and just drag him off his pedestal and see him making love like any common man. We all have private imaginations of that sort. But when it comes to business, to the life that she really leads as distinguished from the life of dreams and fancies, she likes Freddy and she likes the Colonel; and she does not like Higgins and Mr. Doolittle. Galatea never does quite like Pygmalion: his relation to her is too godlike to be altogether agreeable.<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
